 **Lifecycle decision** — in confirm mode, shown before `resume` or `restart`\\n27: \\n28: ### Usage\\n29: \\n30: - **Location:** `{artifact_dir}/deep-research-dashboard.md`\\n31: - **Generated by:** Orchestrator (step_generate_dashboard in YAML workflow)\\n32: - **Data sources:** `deep-research-state.jsonl` + `findings-registry.json` + `d... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1783487959071,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0bfd72ffbffeOJIQWH3C696a5x\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_PnU54vXX97Xqh1CPbmAdEFDG\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md\",\"offset\":1,\"limit\":1000},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n1: ---\\n2: title: Deep Research Strategy Template\\n3: description: Runtime template copied to research/ during initialization to track research progress, focus decisions, and outcomes across iterations.\\n4: trigger_phrases:\\n5:   - \\\"deep research strategy\\\"\\n6:   - \\\"research strategy template\\\"\\n7:   - \\\"research session tracking\\\"\\n8:   - \\\"exhausted research approaches\\\"\\n9:   - \\\"research stop conditions\\\"\\n10:   - \\\"ruled out research directions\\\"\\n11: importance_tier: normal\\n12: contextType: planning\\n13: version: 1.14.0.19\\n14: ---\\n15: \\n16: # Deep Research Strategy - Session Tracking Template\\n17: \\n18: Runtime template copied to `{spec_folder}/research/` during initialization. Tracks research progress across iterations.\\n19: \\n20: ## 1. OVERVIEW\\n21: \\n22: ### Purpose\\n23: \\n24: Serves as the \\\"persistent brain\\\" for a deep research session. Records what to investigate, what worked, what failed, and where to focus next. Read by the orchestrator and agents at every iteration.\\n25: \\n26: ### Usage\\n27: \\n28: - **Init:** Orchestrator copies this template to `{spec_folder}/research/deep-research-strategy.md` and populates Topic, Key Questions, Known Context, and Research Boundaries from config and memory context.\\n29: - **Per iteration:** Agent reads Next Focus, writes iteration evidence, and the reducer refreshes What Worked/Failed, answered questions, carried-forward qu... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"step_finish\",\"timestamp\":1783487959670,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0bfd72ffbffeOJIQWH3C696a5x\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f402a92730017vZ0T95ah2Hj8F\",\"reason\":\"tool-calls\",\"snapshot\":\"7db8730d6abd963fb0f6c6b3e9a0b551e7a8efc6\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f402a6b02001mEWNCv5Gf6ea1s\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_0bfd72ffbffeOJIQWH3C696a5x\",\"type\":\"step-finish\",\"tokens\":{\"total\":60766,\"input\":1979,\"output\":408,\"reasoning\":11,\"cache\":{\"write\":0,\"read\":58368}},\"cost\":0}}\n{\"type\":\"step_start\",\"timestamp\":1783487961323,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0bfd72ffbffeOJIQWH3C696a5x\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f402a98e90010ogV1uOdLhPgCa\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f402a944f0016Dc0r0J7DLVTKV\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_0bfd72ffbffeOJIQWH3C696a5x\",\"snapshot\":\"7db8730d6abd963fb0f6c6b3e9a0b551e7a8efc6\",\"type\":\"step-start\"}}\n{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"timestamp\":1783487964895,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0bfd72ffbffeOJIQWH3C696a5x\",\"part\":{\"type\":\"tool\",\"tool\":\"read\",\"callID\":\"call_yPsLEVeQDv1S76gH9Rnw6WeU\",\"state\":{\"status\":\"completed\",\"input\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml\",\"offset\":737,\"limit\":4000},\"output\":\"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml</path>\\n<type>file</type>\\n<content>\\n737:             values:\\n738:               - \\\"{next_focus}\\\"\\n739:               - \\\"{remaining_questions_list}\\\"\\n740:               - \\\"{carried_forward_open_questions}\\\"\\n741:           recovery:\\n742:             category: \\\"recovery\\\"\\n743:             values:\\n744:               - \\\"{recovery_strategy}\\\"\\n745:               - \\\"{least_explored}\\\"\\n746:           ideas:\\n747:             category: \\\"ideas\\\"\\n748:             values:\\n749:               - \\\"{promoted_ideas_list}\\\"\\n750:             optional_file: \\\"{state_paths.packet_dir}/research-ideas.md\\\"\\n751:         algorithm: |\\n752:           Use registry.rejectedPatternIndex and registry.promotedIdeas from the latest\\n753:           reducer pass as the source of truth.\\n754:           Compare normalized exact text first. Then compare fuzzy similarity with\\n755:           rejected_pattern_fuzzy_threshold, but only when candidate and rejected categories\\n756:           are compatible. Remove suppressed candidates from next_focus, recovery, and ideas\\n757:           selection before rendering the dispatch prompt. If all candidates are suppressed,\\n758:           halt for operator input instead of reusing a rejected idea.\\n759:         outputs:\\n760:           - accepted_next_focus: \\\"First unsuppressed next-focus candidate, or null\\\"\\n761:           - accepted_recovery_candidate: \\\"First unsuppressed recovery candidate, or null\\\"\\n762:           - accepted_idea_candidate... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"step_finish\",\"timestamp\":1783487965873,\"sessionID\":\"ses_0bfd72ffbffeOJIQWH3C696a5x\",\"part\":{\"id\":\"prt_f402aaaaf001ju6ftpnWWu4XmE\",\"reason\":\"tool-calls\",\"snapshot\":\"9e0b9fa9d809e377bbbeb3ba5950c92aedb45b2a\",\"messageID\":\"msg_f402a944f0016Dc0r0J7DLVTKV\",\"sessionID\":\"ses_0bfd72ffbffeOJIQWH3C696a5x\",\"type\":\"step-finish\",\"tokens\":{\"total\":77684,\"input\":17697,\"output\":59,\"reasoning\":24,\"cache\":{\"write\":0,\"read\":59904}},\"cost\":0}}\n{\"type\":\"ste