{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783489291481,"sessionID":"ses_0bfc4afb7ffeA8X2g5OnaG20YL","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_sSzXDtSzsux4THyGopZZCesp","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/spec.md","offset":57,"limit":18},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n57: Three parallel sonnet-5 Plan agents already produced a concrete, file:line-grounded mechanical design for merging `deep-loop-workflows` + `deep-loop-runtime` into `system-deep-loop` (structural layout, reference migration, and the research-fanout invocation itself). That design deserves independent stress-testing across diverse models and reasoning styles before the irreversible directory move (child 002) executes — a single planning pass can share blind spots a genuinely independent second and third look would catch.\n58: \n59: ### Purpose\n60: Run a 20-iteration `/deep:research` fanout across 3 model lineages (10x GPT-5.5 xhigh/fast, 5x GLM-5.2 max, 5x Sonnet-5 xhigh) investigating the merge design, converging on a ranked, evidence-backed set of confirmations, corrections, and open risks that feed directly into child 002/003's execution.\n61: <!-- /ANCHOR:problem -->\n62: \n63: ---\n64: \n65: <!-- ANCHOR:scope -->\n66: ## 3. SCOPE\n67: \n68: ### In Scope\n69: - Read-only, multi-model investigation of the merge design (structural layout, coupling repair, reference migration, advisor-corpus handling, fallback-router wiring).\n70: - Synthesis into `research/research.md` + `research/resource-map.md`, with a `research/fanout-attribution.md` mapping which lineage/replica surfaced which finding.\n71: \n72: ### Out of Scope\n73: - Executing any part of the merge itself (delegated to sibling children 002-005).\n74: - Modifying `deep-loop-workflows`/`deep-loop-runtime` in any way — this phase is strictly read-only investigation.\n\n(Showing lines 57-74 of 135. Use offset=75 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"Three parallel sonnet-5 Plan agents already produced a concrete, file:line-grounded mechanical design for merging `deep-loop-workflows` + `deep-loop-runtime` into `system-deep-loop` (structural layout, reference migration, and the research-fanout invocation itself). That design deserves independent stress-testing across diverse models and reasoning styles before the irreversible directory move (child 002) executes — a single planning pass can share blind spots a genuinely independent second and third look would catch.\n\n### Purpose\nRun a 20-iteration `/deep:research` fanout across 3 model lineages (10x GPT-5.5 xhigh/fast, 5x GLM-5.2 max, 5x Sonnet-5 xhigh) investigating the merge design, converging on a ranked, evidence-backed set of confirmations, corrections, and open risks that feed directly into child 002/003's execution.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:problem -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:scope -->\n## 3. SCOPE\n\n### In Scope\n- Read-only, multi-model investigation of the merge design (structural layout, coupling repair, reference migration, advisor-corpus handling, fallback-router wiring).\n- Synthesis into `research/research.md` + `research/resource-map.md`, with a `research/fanout-attribution.md` mapping which lineage/replica surfaced which finding.\n\n### Out of Scope\n- Executing any part of the merge itself (delegated to sibling children 002-005).\n- Modifying `deep-loop-workflows`/`deep-loop-runtime` in any way — this phase is strictly read-only investigation.","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/spec.md","text":"Three parallel sonnet-5 Plan agents already produced a concrete, file:line-grounded mechanical design for merging `deep-loop-workflows` + `deep-loop-runtime` into `system-deep-loop` (structural layout, reference migration, and the research-fanout invocation itself). That design deserves independent stress-testing across diverse models and reasoning styles before the irreversible directory move (child 002) executes — a single planning pass can share blind spots a genuinely independent second and third look would catch.\n\n### Purpose\nRun a 20-iteration `/deep:research` fanout across 3 model lineages (10x GPT-5.5 xhigh/fast, 5x GLM-5.2 max, 5x Sonnet-5 xhigh) investigating the merge design, converging on a ranked, evidence-backed set of confirmations, corrections, and open risks that feed directly into child 002/003's execution.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:problem -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:scope -->\n## 3. SCOPE\n\n### In Scope\n- Read-only, multi-model investigation of the merge design (structural layout, coupling repair, reference migration, advisor-corpus handling, fallback-router wiring).\n- Synthesis into `research/research.md` + `research/resource-map.md`, with a `research/fanout-attribution.md` mapping which lineage/replica surfaced which finding.\n\n### Out of Scope\n- Executing any part of the merge itself (delegated to sibling children 002-005).\n- Modifying `deep-loop-workflows`/`deep-loop-runtime` in any way — this phase is strictly read-only investigation.","lineStart":57,"lineEnd":74,"totalLines":135,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/spec.md","time":{"start":1783489291473,"end":1783489291480}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0030482e0e0847a3016a4de30b0e9081919974c55baf283a52"}},"id":"prt_f403ee4b000190B3b0Hax48sYm","sessionID":"ses_0bfc4afb7ffeA8X2g5OnaG20YL","messageID":"msg_f403eb9cf001JMD3vgO66fUNnV"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783489291489,"sessionID":"ses_0bfc4afb7ffeA8X2g5OnaG20YL","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_9iYbVR7drfBE9lKXUSLr5JQ4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/spec.md","offset":103,"limit":25},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n103: | REQ-004 | GLM-5.2 failures degrade gracefully, not silently | On `maxRetries` exhaustion for a `glm52-N` replica, `fanout-salvage.cjs` recovers partial output; synthesis notes any lineage that finished with fewer than 5 completed replicas |\n104: | REQ-005 | Sonnet-5 lineage dispatched via `cli-claude-code`, never `kind: native` | Confirmed in the executors payload — `native` fan-out dispatch is hardcoded to `model: opus` in `deep_research_auto.yaml` and would silently produce the wrong model |\n105: <!-- /ANCHOR:requirements -->\n106: \n107: ---\n108: \n109: <!-- ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n110: ## 5. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n111: \n112: - **SC-001**: All 3 lineages reach their per-lineage `minIterations: 3` floor; no lineage terminates with 0 completed replicas.\n113: - **SC-002**: `research/research.md` either confirms child 002/003's staged execution plans as-is, or lists concrete, evidence-backed revisions before those phases start.\n114: - **SC-003**: Any genuinely new risk (beyond what the 3 Plan agents already surfaced) is flagged explicitly, not silently folded into the existing risk list.\n115: <!-- /ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n116: \n117: ---\n118: \n119: <!-- ANCHOR:risks -->\n120: ## 6. RISKS & DEPENDENCIES\n121: \n122: | Type | Item | Impact | Mitigation |\n123: |------|------|--------|------------|\n124: | Risk | GLM-5.2 has no automatic fallback to MiMo-v2.5-Pro wired at the fan-out level (`fallback-router.ts` has zero callers today) | A `glm52-N` replica that exhausts `maxRetries` degrades to a same-model retry-and-salvage, not an automatic model swap | Accepted for this phase; operator-mediated manual re-dispatch as `mimo-v2.5-pro` is possible post-hoc since `fanout-merge.cjs` just enumerates `lineages/` subdirectories — see plan.md §Fallback |\n125: | Risk | `cli-claude-code` self-invocation concerns (a prior barter-packet attempt failed on packet-state-write, unrelated to self-invocation) | Low — `fanout-run.cjs` dispatches via direct `spawnSync`, not the `cli-claude-code` skill; its env allowlist strips `CLAUDECODE`; its recursion guard checks an internal marker, not env/ancestry | Recommend a `count: 1` smoke-test replica before committing all 5 Sonnet-5 replicas (see plan.md) |\n126: | Dependency | 3 parallel sonnet-5 Plan agents' file:line-grounded design (this session) | This research phase validates/extends that design rather than starting from zero | N/A — design already captured in child 002/003's own spec.md/plan.md |\n127: <!-- /ANCHOR:risks -->\n\n(Showing lines 103-127 of 135. Use offset=128 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"| REQ-004 | GLM-5.2 failures degrade gracefully, not silently | On `maxRetries` exhaustion for a `glm52-N` replica, `fanout-salvage.cjs` recovers partial output; synthesis notes any lineage that finished with fewer than 5 completed replicas |\n| REQ-005 | Sonnet-5 lineage dispatched via `cli-claude-code`, never `kind: native` | Confirmed in the executors payload — `native` fan-out dispatch is hardcoded to `model: opus` in `deep_research_auto.yaml` and would silently produce the wrong model |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:requirements -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n## 5. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n\n- **SC-001**: All 3 lineages reach their per-lineage `minIterations: 3` floor; no lineage terminates with 0 completed replicas.\n- **SC-002**: `research/research.md` either confirms child 002/003's staged execution plans as-is, or lists concrete, evidence-backed revisions before those phases start.\n- **SC-003**: Any genuinely new risk (beyond what the 3 Plan agents already surfaced) is flagged explicitly, not silently folded into the existing risk list.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:risks -->\n## 6. RISKS & DEPENDENCIES\n\n| Type | Item | Impact | Mitigation |","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/spec.md","text":"| REQ-004 | GLM-5.2 failures degrade gracefully, not silently | On `maxRetries` exhaustion for a `glm52-N` replica, `fanout-salvage.cjs` recovers partial output; synthesis notes any lineage that finished with fewer than 5 completed replicas |\n| REQ-005 | Sonnet-5 lineage dispatched via `cli-claude-code`, never `kind: native` | Confirmed in the executors payload — `native` fan-out dispatch is hardcoded to `model: opus` in `deep_research_auto.yaml` and would silently produce the wrong model |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:requirements -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n## 5. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n\n- **SC-001**: All 3 lineages reach their per-lineage `minIterations: 3` floor; no lineage terminates with 0 completed replicas.\n- **SC-002**: `research/research.md` either confirms child 002/003's staged execution plans as-is, or lists concrete, evidence-backed revisions before those phases start.\n- **SC-003**: Any genuinely new risk (beyond what the 3 Plan agents already surfaced) is flagged explicitly, not silently folded into the existing risk list.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:success-criteria -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:risks -->\n## 6. RISKS & DEPENDENCIES\n\n| Type | Item | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|------|--------|------------|\n| Risk | GLM-5.2 has no automatic fallback to MiMo-v2.5-Pro wired at the fan-out level (`fallback-router.ts` has zero callers today) | A `glm52-N` replica that exhausts `maxRetries` degrades to a same-model retry-and-salvage, not an automatic model swap | Accepted for this phase; operator-mediated manual re-dispatch as `mimo-v2.5-pro` is possible post-hoc since `fanout-merge.cjs` just enumerates `lineages/` subdirectories — see plan.md §Fallback |\n| Risk | `cli-claude-code` self-invocation concerns (a prior barter-packet attempt failed on packet-state-write, unrelated to self-invocation) | Low — `fanout-run.cjs` dispatches via direct `spawnSync`, not the `cli-claude-code` skill; its env allowlist strips `CLAUDECODE`; its recursion guard checks an internal marker, not env/ancestry | Recommend a `count: 1` smoke-test replica before committing all 5 Sonnet-5 replicas (see plan.md) |\n| Dependency | 3 parallel sonnet-5 Plan agents' file:line-grounded design (this session) | This research phase validates/extends that design rather than starting from zero | N/A — design already captured in child 002/003's own spec.md/plan.md |\n<!-- /ANCHOR:risks -->","lineStart":103,"lineEnd":127,"totalLines":135,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/spec.md","time":{"start":1783489291476,"end":1783489291488}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0030482e0e0847a3016a4de30b0e9881919ab21c0fe53d56ac"}},"id":"prt_f403ee4d3001WDZA0E1qxRKzoV","sessionID":"ses_0bfc4afb7ffeA8X2g5OnaG20YL","messageID":"msg_f403eb9cf001JMD3vgO66fUNnV"}}
