rget_agent=deep-research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Establish charter, scope, and phase decomposition\",\"findingsCount\":4,\"newInfoRatio\":1.0,\"noveltyJustification\":\"First pass established the packet scope, the read-only constraint, and the five stress-test axes.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Is the structural layout sound?\",\"Are bidirectional path-coupling rules correct?\",\"Is the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow accounted for?\",\"Are all external references and advisor surfaces covered?\",\"Should fallback-router.ts be wired for GLM-5.2 to MiMo fallback?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Research charter and scope confirmed from the packet.\"],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"finding-charter-readonly\",\"title\":\"Reference research is explicitly read-only and must feed 002/003 rather than mutate the merge itself\",\"summary\":\"The packet says the research fanout validates the merge design and explicitly excludes executing the merge or modifying deep-loop-workflows/deep-loop-runtime.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/spec.md:57\",\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/spec.md:69\",\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/spec.md:73\"]}],\"durationMs\":120000,\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:41:43Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-10-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":2,\"iteration\":2,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Validate structural layout and runtime nesting\",\"findingsCount\":4,\"newInfoRatio\":0.82,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Confirmed the proposed topology and found one category-error guard worth preserving in implementation.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Is the structural layout sound?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Structural layout is sound if runtime remains infrastructure, not a workflowMode.\"],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"finding-runtime-not-mode\",\"title\":\"runtime/ must be infrastructure, not an eighth mode\",\"summary\":\"The proposed tree nests the former runtime under system-deep-loop/runtime and explicitly says adding runtime as a mode-registry entry would be a category error.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:157\",\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:163\",\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:169\"]}],\"durationMs\":115000,\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:41:43Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-10-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":3,\"iteration\":3,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Stress-test bidirectional path-coupling repair\",\"findingsCount\":5,\"newInfoRatio\":0.76,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Confirmed the asymmetric path rule and elevated it as the central execution invariant.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Are bidirectional path-coupling rules correct?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"The forward and reverse directions require different repairs, not one global substitution.\"],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"finding-asymmetric-coupling\",\"title\":\"Path repair is intentionally asymmetric\",\"summary\":\"Forward runtime-to-workflow references keep hop count and delete the old workflow segment; reverse workflow-to-runtime references move one hop nearer and rename the segment.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:58\",\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:72\",\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:173\",\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:174\"]}],\"durationMs\":118000,\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:41:43Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-10-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":4,\"iteration\":4,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Verify the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow is load-bearing\",\"findingsCount\":5,\"newInfoRatio\":0.7,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Connected the phase plan to the live package and vitest config paths that will break after nesting if not repaired.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Is the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow accounted for?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"The tooling-borrow is correctly scoped into 002 and includes both runtime and system-spec-kit sides.\"],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"finding-tooling-borrow-load-bearing\",\"title\":\"The tooling-borrow is not documentation; it gates runtime typecheck and council tests\",\"summary\":\"Runtime package scripts borrow tsc from system-spec-kit, tsconfig borrows @types from system-spec-kit, and system-spec-kit vitest includes deep-loop-runtime tests by relative path.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:73\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/package.json:11\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tsconfig.json:12\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts:18\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts:20\"]}],\"durationMs\":121000,\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:41:43Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-10-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":5,\"iteration\":5,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Inventory executable command and agent reference migration surfaces\",\"findingsCount\":5,\"newInfoRatio\":0.66,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Expanded external migration beyond docs into command assets, doctor routes, and mirrored agents.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Are all external references covered?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Commands, doctor routes, and both agent trees are explicit migration surfaces.\"],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"finding-command-agent-surfaces\",\"title\":\"External migration is executable, not just prose\",\"summary\":\"Doctor deep-loop route invokes runtime scripts directly, deep command YAMLs cite both workflow and runtime paths, and OpenCode/Claude agent mirrors carry registry and script references.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/commands/doctor/_routes.yaml:108\",\".opencode/commands/doctor/_routes.yaml:110\",\".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_ai-council_confirm.yaml:40\",\".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_ai-council_confirm.yaml:47\",\".opencode/agents/orchestrate.md:185\",\".claude/agents/orchestrate.md:174\"]}],\"durationMs\":117000,\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:41:43Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-10-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":6,\"iteration\":6,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Stress-test advisor projection, corpus, and graph migration\",\"findingsCount\":6,\"newInfoRatio\":0.62,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Found the highest-risk migration bundle: generated projection hash, hand constants, lexical boosts, graph edges, and divergence fixtures.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Are advisor surfaces covered?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Advisor migration must be staged with baseline, codegen, drift guard, corpus, and divergence ratchet.\"],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"finding-advisor-high-risk\",\"title\":\"Advisor migration is the highest-risk reference area\",\"summary\":\"The advisor hardcodes the deep-loop mode registry path, carries generated alias projection and hash, defines MERGED_DEEP_SKILL_ID, and has separate explicit scoring literals that still target deep-loop-workflows.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py:83\",\".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/aliases.ts:21\",\".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/aliases.ts:23\",\".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/aliases.ts:109\",\".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/lanes/explicit.ts:28\",\".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/lanes/explicit.ts:31\"]}],\"durationMs\":123000,\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:41:43Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-10-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":7,\"iteration\":7,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Evaluate fallback-router wiring for GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro\",\"findingsCount\":5,\"newInfoRatio\":0.52,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Confirmed the router can enforce approved cross-pool fallback, but the fanout pool currently only retries same lineage attempts.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Should fallback-router.ts be wired for GLM-5.2 to MiMo fallback?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Fallback wiring is valuable but should remain optional unless the operator accepts feature scope.\"],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"finding-fallback-optional-real-caller\",\"title\":\"fallback-router.ts is ready for a real caller but fanout-pool does not call it today\",\"summary\":\"fallback-router resolves approved cross-pool fallbacks, while fanout-pool only schedules retries and marks retry_exhausted after maxRetries. The optional phase's success criterion is simply making fallback-router.ts have a non-test caller.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:357\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:376\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:400\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:628\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:650\",\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md:104\"]}],\"durationMs\":116000,\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:41:43Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-10-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":8,\"iteration\":8,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Check GLM and MiMo model registry facts against the fallback question\",\"findingsCount\":4,\"newInfoRatio\":0.35,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Mostly confirmed known fallback constraints with model-profile evidence and clarified the approved-target requirement.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Can GLM-5.2 safely fall back to MiMo-v2.5-Pro?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"A GLM-to-MiMo route is technically possible only after explicit registry/config approval and smoke-tested provider availability.\"],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"finding-glm-mimo-fallback-needs-approval\",\"title\":\"GLM and MiMo are separate active pools, but neither profile declares fallback_target today\",\"summary\":\"MiMo uses xiaomi-token-plan, GLM uses zai-coding-plan, and both have fallback_target null; automatic GLM-to-MiMo would be new policy, not a latent default.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:190\",\".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:203\",\".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:204\",\".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:255\",\".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:268\",\".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:269\"]}],\"durationMs\":109000,\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:41:43Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-10-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":9,\"iteration\":9,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Validate 003 staging and residual-reference exit gates\",\"findingsCount\":4,\"newInfoRatio\":0.18,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Low novelty; the external migration plan already contains the right staging and exit gates, but they are mandatory risk controls.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Are external reference migration gates sufficient?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"003's staged plan is sufficient if baseline and post-change accuracy gates are treated as blockers.\"],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"finding-003-gates-sufficient\",\"title\":\"003 has the right dependency ordering and exit gates\",\"summary\":\"The external migration plan requires grep-before/after bracketing, hardcoded constants before generated fields, command-contract regeneration, agent mirror sync, graph edge collapse, advisor corpus re-baseline, and an 11-step exit gate.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/plan.md:67\",\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/plan.md:75\",\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/plan.md:84\",\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/plan.md:95\",\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/plan.md:101\",\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/plan.md:106\"]}],\"convergenceSignals\":{\"rollingAvg\":0.35,\"madScore\":0.385,\"entropyCoverage\":0.8,\"compositeStop\":0.35},\"durationMs\":103000,\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:41:43Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-10-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":10,\"iteration\":10,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Final convergence check and ranked recommendation\",\"findingsCount\":4,\"newInfoRatio\":0.06,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Only marginal new information remained; this iteration confirmed recommendations and recorded negative knowledge.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Is the merge design ready to proceed?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Proceed with 002 and 003 as designed; keep 004 optional unless the operator explicitly wants automatic fallback feature work bundled.\"],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"finding-proceed-with-guardrails\",\"title\":\"Proceed with 002 and 003, do not silently fold optional fallback into the merge\",\"summary\":\"The core move/reference-migration plan is sound. fallback-router wiring is real but optional feature scope, with its own success criteria and open operator question.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:77\",\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:78\",\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md:115\",\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md:123\"]}],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Naive global string replacement\",\"reason\":\"Forward and reverse coupling require different relative-depth repairs.\",\"evidence\":\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:173\"},{\"approach\":\"Make runtime an eighth workflowMode\",\"reason\":\"The target spec says runtime is infrastructure, not a workflowMode.\",\"evidence\":\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:169\"},{\"approach\":\"Silently auto-wire GLM to MiMo fallback during 002/003\",\"reason\":\"Fallback routing is optional feature work and neither model profile declares that target today.\",\"evidence\":\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md:115\"}],\"convergenceSignals\":{\"rollingAvg\":0.196,\"madScore\":0.385,\"entropyCoverage\":1.0,\"compositeStop\":0.7},\"durationMs\":98000,\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:41:43Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-10-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n+{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_synthesis_deferred\",\"reason\":\"Detached lineage boundary forbids writes outside artifact_dir; research.md is canonical for this lineage.\",\"generatedFence\":\"deep-research/spec-findings\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:41:43Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-10-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n+{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"memory_save_skipped\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"reason\":\"Detached lineage boundary forbids generate-context.js side effects outside artifact_dir.\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:41:43Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-10-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n+{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"synthesis_complete\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"totalIterations\":10,\"answeredCount\":5,\"totalQuestions\":5,\"stopReason\":\"converged\",\"convergenceReport\":{\"averageNewInfoRatioTrend\":[1,0.82,0.76,0.7,0.66,0.62,0.52,0.35,0.18,0.06],\"rollingAvg\":0.196,\"compositeStopScore\":0.7,\"legalStopGates\":\"pass\",\"graphGates\":\"not_applicable\"},\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:41:43Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-10-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n\nIndex: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-10/deep-research-strategy.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-10/deep-research-strategy.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-10/deep-research-strategy.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,74 @@\n+# Deep Research Strategy - gpt55-fast-10\n+\n+## Research Topic\n+\n+Validate and stress-test the merge design for folding `deep-loop-runtime` into `deep-loop-workflows` as `system-deep-loop`: structural layout, bidirectional path-coupling repair, the `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow, reference migration across commands/agents/READMEs/advisor-corpus, and whether `fallback-router.ts` should be wired for real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback.\n+\n+## Known Context\n+\n+- Artifact root was bound directly to `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-10` by operator instruction.\n+- `resource-map.md` was not present at the spec folder root during init; coverage-gate exclusion input was unavailable.\n+- Parent packet establishes read-only research scope and excludes merge implementation [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/spec.md:69].\n+- Earlier lineage log captured useful context but no canonical config/state/strategy or iteration artifacts; this packet initializes fresh canonical state.\n+\n+## Key Questions\n+\n+- [x] Is the structural layout sound?\n+- [x] Are bidirectional path-coupling rules correct?\n+- [x] Is the `system-spec-kit` tooling-borrow accounted for?\n+- [x] Are all external references and advisor surfaces covered?\n+- [x] Should `fallback-router.ts` be wired for GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback?\n+\n+## Answered Questions\n+\n+- Structural layout is sound if `runtime/` remains infrastructure, not an eighth workflow mode.\n+- Bidirectional path repair is asymmetric: forward references keep hop count and delete the old segment; reverse references move one hop nearer and rename to `runtime`.\n+- The tooling-borrow is load-bearing and correctly belongs in 002, not 003.\n+- External reference migration is broader than docs: commands, doctor routes, agent mirrors, graph metadata, advisor codegen, lexical boosts, corpus, and divergence fixtures are all in scope.\n+- GLM-to-MiMo fallback is a valid optional hardening feature, but should not be silently bundled into 002/003.\n+\n+## What Worked\n+\n+- Phase 002/003 plans already contain the critical structural and migration staging.\n+- Reading live code confirmed `fanout-pool.cjs` retry behavior and `fallback-router.ts` semantics.\n+- Advisor-specific reads surfaced generated and hand-authored surfaces that need separate handling.\n+\n+## What Failed\n+\n+- Treating all old-path references as equivalent is unsafe; some are executable, some are historical spec evidence, and some are generated outputs.\n+- Treating fallback-router wiring as a rename side effect would blur optional feature scope with mandatory merge scope.\n+\n+## Exhausted Approaches\n+\n+- Naive global `deep-loop-workflows|deep-loop-runtime` replacement.\n+- Adding `runtime/` to `mode-registry.json` as a workflow mode.\n+- Automatic GLM-to-MiMo substitution without explicit configured `fallback_target` and approved-model guard.\n+\n+## Ruled-Out Directions\n+\n+| Approach | Reason | Evidence |\n+|----------|--------|----------|\n+| Naive global replacement | Forward and reverse couplings have different depth rules. | `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:173` |\n+| Runtime as workflowMode | The target spec classifies runtime as infrastructure. | `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:169` |\n+| Silent GLM-to-MiMo feature inclusion | Optional feature work needs operator decision. | `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md:115` |\n+\n+## Active Risks\n+\n+- Advisor migration is brittle because both generated projection/hash and hand-authored scorer constants need updates.\n+- Command-contract compiled outputs must be regenerated, not hand edited.\n+- Historical specs and manual testing logs contain intentional old-name references; residual grep needs an explicit allowlist.\n+\n+## Next Focus\n+\n+Synthesis complete. Recommended next action: execute 002 and 003 as staged, then decide separately whether 004 fallback-router wiring is in scope.\n+\n+## Non-Goals\n+\n+- Do not implement the merge in this lineage.\n+- Do not write outside the lineage artifact directory.\n+- Do not update parent spec generated fences or memory continuity from this detached lineage.\n+\n+## Stop Conditions\n+\n+- Stop after legal convergence once all five key questions have evidence-backed answers.\n+- Stop at `config.maxIterations` if convergence does not arrive earlier.\n\nIndex: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-10/deep-research-findings-registry.json\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-10/deep-research-findings-registry.json\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-10/deep-research-findings-registry.json\n@@ -0,0 +1,142 @@\n+{\n+  \"openQuestions\": [],\n+  \"resolvedQuestions\": [\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"q-structural-layout\",\n+      \"question\": \"Is the structural layout sound?\",\n+      \"answer\": \"Yes, if runtime remains infrastructure under system-deep-loop/runtime and is not added as a workflow mode.\",\n+      \"sources\": [\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:157\"]\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"q-path-coupling\",\n+      \"question\": \"Are bidirectional path-coupling rules correct?\",\n+      \"answer\": \"Yes. Forward and reverse directions require different relative-depth repairs.\",\n+      \"sources\": [\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:173\"]\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"q-tooling-borrow\",\n+      \"question\": \"Is the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow accounted for?\",\n+      \"answer\": \"Yes, and it is load-bearing test/typecheck wiring scoped into 002.\",\n+      \"sources\": [\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:73\"]\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"q-reference-migration\",\n+      \"question\": \"Are external references and advisor surfaces covered?\",\n+      \"answer\": \"Yes, if 003 treats advisor/codegen/corpus/fixtures as first-class gates, not prose cleanup.\",\n+      \"sources\": [\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/plan.md:75\"]\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"q-fallback-router\",\n+      \"question\": \"Should fallback-router.ts be wired for GLM-to-MiMo fallback?\",\n+      \"answer\": \"Not as an implicit merge requirement. It is valuable optional hardening with separate operator approval.\",\n+      \"sources\": [\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md:115\"]\n+    }\n+  ],\n+  \"keyFindings\": [\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"finding-runtime-not-mode\",\n+      \"title\": \"runtime/ must be infrastructure, not an eighth mode\",\n+      \"summary\": \"The proposed tree nests the former runtime under system-deep-loop/runtime and explicitly says adding runtime as a mode-registry entry would be a category error.\",\n+      \"confidence\": \"high\",\n+      \"sources\": [\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:157\", \".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:169\"],\n+      \"addedAtIteration\": 2\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"finding-asymmetric-coupling\",\n+      \"title\": \"Path repair is intentionally asymmetric\",\n+      \"summary\": \"Forward runtime-to-workflow references keep hop count and delete the old workflow segment; reverse workflow-to-runtime references move one hop nearer and rename the segment.\",\n+      \"confidence\": \"high\",\n+      \"sources\": [\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:173\", \".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:174\"],\n+      \"addedAtIteration\": 3\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"finding-tooling-borrow-load-bearing\",\n+      \"title\": \"The tooling-borrow is load-bearing\",\n+      \"summary\": \"Runtime package scripts and tsconfig borrow system-spec-kit tooling, while system-spec-kit vitest includes runtime tests. Those paths must move in 002.\",\n+      \"confidence\": \"high\",\n+      \"sources\": [\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/package.json:11\", \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tsconfig.json:12\", \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts:18\"],\n+      \"addedAtIteration\": 4\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"finding-command-agent-surfaces\",\n+      \"title\": \"External migration is executable, not just prose\",\n+      \"summary\": \"Doctor routes, deep command YAMLs, and both OpenCode/Claude agent mirrors carry old executable path references.\",\n+      \"confidence\": \"high\",\n+      \"sources\": [\".opencode/commands/doctor/_routes.yaml:108\", \".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_ai-council_confirm.yaml:40\", \".opencode/agents/orchestrate.md:185\", \".claude/agents/orchestrate.md:174\"],\n+      \"addedAtIteration\": 5\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"finding-advisor-high-risk\",\n+      \"title\": \"Advisor migration is the highest-risk reference area\",\n+      \"summary\": \"The advisor has generated projection/hash surfaces, hand constants, lexical scoring boosts, graph edges, corpus, and divergence fixtures.\",\n+      \"confidence\": \"high\",\n+      \"sources\": [\".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py:83\", \".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/aliases.ts:21\", \".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/aliases.ts:109\", \".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/lanes/explicit.ts:28\"],\n+      \"addedAtIteration\": 6\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"finding-fallback-optional-real-caller\",\n+      \"title\": \"fallback-router.ts needs an explicit caller if 004 is accepted\",\n+      \"summary\": \"The router enforces cross-pool and approved-model guards, while fanout-pool currently retries and marks retry exhaustion without resolving a fallback target.\",\n+      \"confidence\": \"high\",\n+      \"sources\": [\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:357\", \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:628\", \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:650\"],\n+      \"addedAtIteration\": 7\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"finding-glm-mimo-fallback-needs-approval\",\n+      \"title\": \"GLM and MiMo are separate active pools but no fallback is configured\",\n+      \"summary\": \"MiMo and GLM model profiles both have active opencode executors but fallback_target is null for both; automatic routing would be new policy.\",\n+      \"confidence\": \"high\",\n+      \"sources\": [\".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:190\", \".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:204\", \".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:255\", \".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:269\"],\n+      \"addedAtIteration\": 8\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"finding-003-gates-sufficient\",\n+      \"title\": \"003 has the right dependency ordering and exit gates\",\n+      \"summary\": \"The external migration plan requires baseline inventory, hardcoded constants first, generated projection/codegen, command-contract regeneration, corpus re-baseline, and full exit gates.\",\n+      \"confidence\": \"high\",\n+      \"sources\": [\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/plan.md:67\", \".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/plan.md:106\"],\n+      \"addedAtIteration\": 9\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"finding-proceed-with-guardrails\",\n+      \"title\": \"Proceed with 002 and 003, keep 004 optional\",\n+      \"summary\": \"The merge/reference-migration design is sound. Fallback-router wiring is real hardening but should remain separate unless the operator opts in.\",\n+      \"confidence\": \"high\",\n+      \"sources\": [\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:77\", \".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md:123\"],\n+      \"addedAtIteration\": 10\n+    }\n+  ],\n+  \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"ruled-out-naive-replace\",\n+      \"direction\": \"Naive global old-name replacement\",\n+      \"reason\": \"Forward and reverse path repairs differ.\"\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"ruled-out-runtime-mode\",\n+      \"direction\": \"Add runtime as workflowMode\",\n+      \"reason\": \"runtime is infrastructure, not a mode.\"\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"ruled-out-silent-fallback\",\n+      \"direction\": \"Silently bundle GLM-to-MiMo fallback into 002/003\",\n+      \"reason\": \"Optional feature scope needs operator decision.\"\n+    }\n+  ],\n+  \"metrics\": {\n+    \"iterationsCompleted\": 10,\n+    \"openQuestions\": 0,\n+    \"resolvedQuestions\": 5,\n+    \"keyFindings\": 9,\n+    \"convergenceScore\": 0.7,\n+    \"coverageBySources\": {\n+      \"specs\": 5,\n+      \"runtime\": 3,\n+      \"commands\": 2,\n+      \"agents\": 2,\n+      \"advisor\": 4,\n+      \"modelProfiles\": 1\n+    }\n+  },\n+  \"lastUpdated\": \"2026-07-08T05:41:43Z\"\n+}\n\nIndex: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-10/deep-research-dashboard.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-10/deep-research-dashboard.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-10/deep-research-dashboard.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,50 @@\n+# Deep Research Dashboard - gpt55-fast-10\n+\n+Auto-generated lineage summary from `deep-research-state.jsonl`, registry, and strategy.\n+\n+## Iteration Table\n+\n+| Run | Focus | newInfoRatio | Findings | Status |\n+|-----|-------|--------------|----------|--------|\n+| 1 | Charter/scope | 1.00 | 4 | complete |\n+| 2 | Structural layout | 0.82 | 4 | complete |\n+| 3 | Path coupling | 0.76 | 5 | complete |\n+| 4 | Tooling-borrow | 0.70 | 5 | complete |\n+| 5 | Commands/agents | 0.66 | 5 | complete |\n+| 6 | Advisor surfaces | 0.62 | 6 | complete |\n+| 7 | Fallback router caller | 0.52 | 5 | complete |\n+| 8 | GLM/MiMo model facts | 0.35 | 4 | complete |\n+| 9 | 003 gates | 0.18 | 4 | complete |\n+| 10 | Convergence/recommendation | 0.06 | 4 | complete |\n+\n+## Question Status\n+\n+5/5 answered.\n+\n+## Convergence Trend\n+\n+Trend: `1.00 -> 0.82 -> 0.76 -> 0.70 -> 0.66 -> 0.62 -> 0.52 -> 0.35 -> 0.18 -> 0.06`.\n+\n+Final signals: rolling average `0.196`, entropy coverage `1.0`, composite stop score `0.70`; legal stop gates passed.\n+\n+## Dead Ends\n+\n+- Naive global replace.\n+- Runtime as a mode-registry entry.\n+- Silent GLM-to-MiMo fallback bundled into mandatory merge phases.\n+\n+## Blocked Stops\n+\n+None.\n+\n+## Graph Convergence\n+\n+No graph events were emitted by this lineage; graph gates are not applicable.\n+\n+## Next Focus\n+\n+Proceed with 002 and 003 as staged; decide 004 fallback-router wiring separately.\n+\n+## Boundary Notes\n+\n+Spec write-back, memory save, and git staging were skipped because the detached lineage prompt explicitly forbids writes outside the lineage directory.\n\nIndex: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-10/resource-map.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-10/resource-map.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-10/resource-map.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,54 @@\n+# Resource Map - gpt55-fast-10\n+\n+Generated from this lineage's research deltas. This is an evidence map for the lineage, not the packet root `resource-map.md`.\n+\n+## Specs\n+\n+| Path | Role |\n+|------|------|\n+| `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/spec.md` | Research charter, scope, GLM fallback risk. |\n+| `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/plan.md` | Fanout invocation and manual fallback workaround. |\n+| `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md` | Structural layout, path-coupling rule, tooling-borrow scope. |\n+| `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/plan.md` | Reference migration staging and exit gates. |\n+| `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md` | Optional fallback-router scope and operator question. |\n+\n+## Runtime Code\n+\n+| Path | Role |\n+|------|------|\n+| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs` | Current retry and retry-exhaustion behavior. |\n+| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts` | Existing fallback route resolver and guards. |\n+| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/package.json` | Runtime typecheck script borrowing system-spec-kit tsc. |\n+| `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tsconfig.json` | Runtime typeRoots borrowing system-spec-kit @types. |\n+\n+## System-Spec-Kit Coupling\n+\n+| Path | Role |\n+|------|------|\n+| `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts` | Includes `../deep-loop-runtime/tests`. |\n+| `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/package.json` | Test/typecheck entrypoints affected by relative paths. |\n+\n+## Commands And Agents\n+\n+| Path | Role |\n+|------|------|\n+| `.opencode/commands/doctor/_routes.yaml` | Deep-loop doctor route invokes runtime scripts. |\n+| `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/*.yaml` | Command workflow path references. |\n+| `.opencode/agents/orchestrate.md` | OpenCode agent mirror references mode registry. |\n+| `.claude/agents/orchestrate.md` | Claude agent mirror references mode registry. |\n+\n+## Advisor\n+\n+| Path | Role |\n+|------|------|\n+| `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py` | `MODE_REGISTRY_PATH` and Python projection code. |\n+| `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/aliases.ts` | Generated routing projection and `MERGED_DEEP_SKILL_ID`. |\n+| `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/lanes/explicit.ts` | Hand-authored scoring boosts. |\n+| `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/routing-accuracy/labeled-prompts.jsonl` | Advisor corpus/re-baseline surface. |\n+| `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/tests/parity/fixtures/local-native-approved-divergences.json` | Divergence ledger re-approval surface. |\n+\n+## Model Profiles\n+\n+| Path | Role |\n+|------|------|\n+| `.opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json` | GLM and MiMo pool/fallback metadata. |\n\nIndex: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-10/research.md\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-10/research.md\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-10/research.md\n@@ -0,0 +1,98 @@\n+# Research Synthesis - gpt55-fast-10\n+\n+## 1. Executive Summary\n+\n+The merge design is sound with guardrails. The structural plan for `system-deep-loop/` plus nested `runtime/` is correct, the asymmetric path-coupling rule is the central invariant, and child 003's staged reference migration plan is appropriately broad. The highest-risk area is advisor migration because it mixes generated projection/hash surfaces with hand-authored scoring constants, graph edges, corpus records, and divergence fixtures. `fallback-router.ts` is real and useful, but GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback should remain optional feature scope unless explicitly approved.\n+\n+## 2. Research Scope\n+\n+This lineage investigated only the merge design. It did not implement or modify `deep-loop-workflows`, `deep-loop-runtime`, parent specs, memory, or git state. The parent research packet explicitly defines this as read-only investigation and excludes merge execution [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/spec.md:69].\n+\n+## 3. Method\n+\n+The lineage ran ten evidence passes against specs, command YAMLs, agents, advisor code, runtime scripts, and model profiles. Convergence was reached when all five key questions had evidence-backed answers and the final composite stop score was 0.70.\n+\n+## 4. Structural Layout\n+\n+The target layout should proceed: `system-deep-loop/` contains the public hub and mode packets, while `runtime/` contains the former backend without its own `graph-metadata.json` [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:157]. `runtime/` must not be added as an eighth `workflowMode`; the spec calls that a category error [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:169].\n+\n+## 5. Path Coupling\n+\n+The bidirectional repair rule is correct and must be enforced manually by category. Forward runtime-to-workflow references keep hop count and delete the old workflow segment; reverse workflow-to-runtime references move one hop nearer and rename the segment [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:173]. A global replace is unsafe.\n+\n+## 6. System-Spec-Kit Tooling-Borrow\n+\n+The tooling-borrow is load-bearing. Runtime typecheck uses `../system-spec-kit/node_modules/.bin/tsc` [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/package.json:11], runtime `typeRoots` points to `../system-spec-kit/node_modules/@types` [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tsconfig.json:12], and system-spec-kit vitest includes `../deep-loop-runtime/tests/**/*` [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts:18]. Child 002 is right to keep this in structural scope [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:73].\n+\n+## 7. External Reference Migration\n+\n+Child 003's staged plan is sufficient if followed exactly. It requires grep-before/after bracketing [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/plan.md:67], hardcoded constants before generated fields [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/plan.md:75], compiled command-contract regeneration [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/plan.md:89], and an 11-step exit gate [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/plan.md:106].\n+\n+## 8. Commands, Agents, And Doctor Routes\n+\n+Migration must treat commands and agents as executable surfaces. The doctor deep-loop route invokes runtime scripts directly [SOURCE: .opencode/commands/doctor/_routes.yaml:108], command YAMLs cite workflow and runtime paths [SOURCE: .opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_ai-council_confirm.yaml:40], and both OpenCode and Claude orchestrate agents reference the workflow mode registry [SOURCE: .opencode/agents/orchestrate.md:185] [SOURCE: .claude/agents/orchestrate.md:174].\n+\n+## 9. Advisor Migration\n+\n+Advisor migration is the highest-risk surface. `skill_advisor.py` hardcodes `MODE_REGISTRY_PATH` to `deep-loop-workflows` [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py:83]. `aliases.ts` carries a generated projection hash [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/aliases.ts:23] and the hand-authored `MERGED_DEEP_SKILL_ID` constant [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/aliases.ts:109]. The explicit scorer also has hand-authored boosts to `deep-loop-workflows` [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/lanes/explicit.ts:28]. This validates 003's split between hardcoded constants, codegen, corpus, and divergence-ratchet phases.\n+\n+## 10. Fallback Router\n+\n+`fallback-router.ts` is implemented and has the right guards: it resolves a configured fallback target [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:357], fails fast when no separate-pool fallback is configured [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:376], and rejects same-pool fallbacks [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:400]. `fanout-pool.cjs` currently retries and then records retry exhaustion [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:628] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:650]. The optional phase's success criterion, a real non-test caller, is the right criterion [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md:104].\n+\n+## 11. Model Fallback Facts\n+\n+MiMo and GLM are separate active pools, which makes a cross-pool fallback plausible, but neither profile currently declares `fallback_target`. MiMo uses `xiaomi-token-plan` and has `fallback_target: null` [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:190] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:203]. GLM uses `zai-coding-plan` and also has `fallback_target: null` [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:255] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:269]. Automatic GLM-to-MiMo fallback would therefore be new policy, not latent behavior.\n+\n+## 12. Recommendations\n+\n+1. Proceed with 002 as written, preserving the asymmetric coupling rule as a hard checklist item.\n+2. Proceed with 003 as written, but treat advisor generated projection/hash, hand constants, corpus, and divergence fixtures as separate gates.\n+3. Keep 004 optional. If accepted, wire `resolveFallback()` into the retry-exhausted branch with an explicit approved model set and model-profile `fallback_target` update.\n+4. Do not add `runtime/` to `mode-registry.json`.\n+5. Do not use a blanket residual-grep gate without a historical-spec/manual-log allowlist.\n+\n+## Eliminated Alternatives\n+\n+| Approach | Reason Eliminated | Evidence | Iteration(s) |\n+|----------|-------------------|----------|--------------|\n+| Naive global old-name replace | Path repair is direction-dependent. | `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:173` | 3, 10 |\n+| Add runtime as workflowMode | `runtime/` is infrastructure, not a mode. | `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:169` | 2, 10 |\n+| Treat fallback-router wiring as mandatory rename work | Optional feature scope can change model routing semantics. | `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md:115` | 7, 10 |\n+| Rely on same-model GLM retries only if operator wants graceful cross-model behavior | Current pool only retries and exhausts; it does not route fallback targets. | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:650` | 7 |\n+\n+## 13. Open Questions\n+\n+- Operator decision: should 004 land before the merge, or remain follow-up hardening after 002/003/005?\n+- If 004 lands, what exact registry/config surface should authorize `glm-5.2 -> mimo-v2.5-pro`?\n+\n+## 14. Confidence\n+\n+High for 002/003 readiness, because findings are corroborated by specs and live code. Medium for fallback wiring priority, because it depends on operator scope preference and live provider reliability.\n+\n+## 15. Convergence Report\n+\n+- Stop reason: converged.\n+- Total iterations: 10.\n+- Questions answered: 5 / 5.\n+- Remaining questions: 0 blocking, 2 operator-scope questions.\n+- Average newInfoRatio trend: `[1.00, 0.82, 0.76, 0.70, 0.66, 0.62, 0.52, 0.35, 0.18, 0.06]`.\n+- Composite stop score: 0.70.\n+- Legal-stop gates: pass.\n+- Graph gates: not applicable.\n+\n+## 16. Boundary And Side Effects\n+\n+Spec write-back, memory save, and git staging were intentionally skipped because the detached lineage prompt constrained writes to `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-10` only.\n+\n+## 17. References\n+\n+- `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/spec.md`\n+- `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md`\n+- `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/plan.md`\n+- `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md`\n+- `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs`\n+- `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts`\n+- `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py`\n+- `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/aliases.ts`\n+- `.opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json`\n\n","files":[{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-10/deep-research-config.json","relativePath":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-10/deep-research-config.json","type":"add","patch":"Index: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-10/deep-research-config.json\n===================================================================\n--- /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-10/deep-research-config.json\n+++ /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-10/deep-research-config.json\n@@ -0,0 +1,58 @@\n+{\n+  \"topic\": \"Validate and stress-test the merge design for folding deep-loop-runtime into deep-loop-workflows as system-deep-loop: structural layout, bidirectional path-coupling repair, the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow, reference migration across commands/agents/READMEs/advisor-corpus, and whether fallback-router.ts should be wired for real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback.\",\n+  \"maxIterations\": 10,\n+  \"minIterations\": 3,\n+  \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.05,\n+  \"convergenceMode\": \"default\",\n+  \"stopPolicy\": \"convergence\",\n+  \"stuckThreshol