{"type":"text","timestamp":1783489694497,"sessionID":"ses_0bfc4afb7ffeA8X2g5OnaG20YL","part":{"id":"prt_f4044e1d6001wPGUHGLfhrpoA4","messageID":"msg_f4044d0c5001HtMB4qPNkZw60i","sessionID":"ses_0bfc4afb7ffeA8X2g5OnaG20YL","type":"text","text":"Current lineage has the top-level state/config/synthesis files only; the `iterations/` and `deltas/` artifacts are absent from the glob output.","time":{"start":1783489683926,"end":1783489694494},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_0d603b1683f4755e016a4de493ec508191932837e08f7e69c1","phase":"commentary"}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783489694565,"sessionID":"ses_0bfc4afb7ffeA8X2g5OnaG20YL","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_MX6UwFadp94GjxaBgaPE1kvh","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/quick_reference.md","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/quick_reference.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Research Quick Reference\n3: description: One-page cheat sheet for the autonomous deep research loop.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep research quick reference\"\n6:   - \"research loop cheat sheet\"\n7:   - \"research iteration checklist\"\n8:   - \"research loop troubleshooting\"\n9:   - \"research tuning guide\"\n10:   - \"research progress visualization\"\n11: importance_tier: normal\n12: contextType: general\n13: version: 1.14.0.26\n14: ---\n15: \n16: # Deep Research Quick Reference\n17: \n18: One-page operator cheat sheet for the autonomous deep research loop.\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n23: \n24: Lookup surface during runs covering when to invoke the loop, what each phase produces, how convergence is computed, and where live state lives on disk. Defer to the full protocol and convergence references for deep reasoning.\n25: \n26: Operator contract source of truth for this page:\n27: - command syntax: `.opencode/commands/deep/research.md`\n28: - convergence stop contract: `references/convergence/convergence.md`, `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md`, and the deep-research YAML workflow\n29: - state packet contract: `references/state/state_format.md`, `references/state/state_jsonl.md`, `references/state/state_outputs.md`, and `references/state/state_reducer_registry.md`\n30: \n31: ---\n32: \n33: ## 2. COMMANDS\n34: \n35: | Command | Description |\n36: |---------|-------------|\n37: | `/deep:research:auto \"topic\"` | Run autonomous deep research (no approval gates) |\n38: | `/deep:research:confirm \"topic\"` | Run with approval gates at each iteration |\n39: | `/deep:research \"topic\"` | Ask which mode to use |\n40: \n41: ### Parameters\n42: \n43: | Parameter | Default | Description |\n44: |-----------|---------|-------------|\n45: | `--max-iterations` | 10 | Maximum loop iterations |\n46: | `--convergence` | 0.05 | Stop when avg newInfoRatio below this |\n47: | `--spec-folder` | auto | Target spec folder path |\n48: | `progressiveSynthesis` | true | Allow incremental `research/research.md` updates before final synthesis |\n49: \n50: ---\n51: \n52: ## 3. WHEN TO USE\n53: \n54: | Scenario | Use |\n55: |----------|-----|\n56: | Deep unknown topic, multi-round needed | `/deep:research` |\n57: | Simple question, 1-2 sources | Direct search with `@context` |\n58: | Check prior work only | `memory_context()` |\n59: | Exhaustive critical research | `/deep:research --max-iterations 15 --convergence 0.02` |\n60: \n61: ---\n62: \n63: ## 4. ARCHITECTURE\n64: \n65: ```text\n66: /deep:research  -->  YAML workflow  -->  @deep-research agent (LEAF)\n67:     |                    |                      |\n68:     |                    |                      +-- Read state\n69:     |                    |                      +-- Research (3-5 actions)\n70:     |                    |                      +-- Write findings\n71:     |                    |                      +-- Update state\n72:     |                    |\n73:     |                    +-- Init (config, strategy, state)\n74:     |                    +-- Loop (dispatch, evaluate, decide)\n75:     |                    +-- Synthesize (final research/research.md)\n76:     |                    +-- Save (memory context)\n77: ```\n78: \n79: ---\n80: \n81: ## 5. STATE FILES\n82: \n83: | File | Location | Format | Purpose |\n84: |------|----------|--------|---------|\n85: | Config | `research/deep-research-config.json` | JSON | Loop parameters |\n86: | State | `research/deep-research-state.jsonl` | JSONL | Iteration log (append-only) |\n87: | Strategy | `research/deep-research-strategy.md` | Markdown | What worked/failed, next focus |\n88: | Registry | `research/findings-registry.json` | JSON | Reducer-owned open/resolved questions and key findings |\n89: | Dashboard | `research/deep-research-dashboard.md` | Markdown | Reducer-owned lifecycle and convergence summary |\n90: | Iterations | `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Markdown | Per-iteration findings |\n91: | Output | `research/research.md` | Markdown | Workflow-owned progressive synthesis output |\n92: \n93: > **Live lifecycle branches:** `resume`, `restart`. (`fork` and `completed-continue` are deferred and not runtime-wired.) `progressiveSynthesis` defaults to `true`, so `research/research.md` is updated during the loop and finalized at synthesis.\n94: \n95: > **Path contract:** root-spec runs write directly to `{spec_folder}/research/`; child-phase and sub-phase first runs use the local `{spec_folder}/research/` directory directly, with `{ownerSlug}-pt-NN` allocated only when prior non-matching content already exists.\n96: \n97: > **Canonical pause sentinel:** `research/.deep-research-pause`\n98: \n99: > **Runtime capability matrix:** `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/capability_matrix.md` and `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/runtime_capabilities.json`\n100: \n101: ---\n102: \n103: ## 6. ITERATION STATUS LEGEND\n104: \n105: | Status | Meaning |\n106: |--------|---------|\n107: | `complete` | Normal iteration with findings |\n108: | `timeout` | Exceeded time/tool budget |\n109: | `error` | Failed to produce outputs |\n110: | `stuck` | No new information found |\n111: | `insight` | Low ratio but conceptual breakthrough |\n112: | `thought` | Analytical-only, no evidence |\n113: \n114: ---\n115: \n116: ## 7. CONVERGENCE DECISION TREE\n117: \n118: ```text\n119: Max iterations reached?\n120:   Yes --> STOP\n121: \n122: All questions answered?\n123:   Yes --> STOP\n124: \n125: stuckThreshold consecutive no-progress?\n126:   Yes --> STUCK_RECOVERY\n127:     Recovery works? --> CONTINUE\n128:     Recovery fails? --> STOP (with gaps)\n129: \n130: Composite convergence (3-signal weighted > 0.60)?\n131:   Yes --> STOP (converged)\n132: \n133: Otherwise --> CONTINUE\n134: ```\n135: \n136: ### 3-Signal Convergence Model\n137: \n138: | Signal | Weight | Min Iterations | Votes STOP When |\n139: |--------|--------|---------------|-----------------|\n140: | Rolling Average | 0.30 | 3 | avg(last 3 newInfoRatios) < convergenceThreshold |\n141: | MAD Noise Floor | 0.35 | 4 | latest ratio <= MAD * 1.4826 |\n142: | Question Entropy | 0.35 | 1 | answered / total questions >= 0.85 |\n143: \n144: **Composite stop threshold:** 0.60 -- weighted stop score must exceed this before quality guards are evaluated.\n145: \n146: Quality guards (source diversity, focus alignment, no single-weak-source) must pass before STOP.\n147: \n148: ---\n149: \n150: ## 8. AGENT ITERATION CHECKLIST\n151: \n152: Each @deep-research iteration:\n153: 1. Read `deep-research-state.jsonl` and `deep-research-strategy.md`\n154: 2. Determine focus from reducer-owned strategy \"Next Focus\"\n155: 3. Execute 3-5 research actions (WebFetch, Grep, Read, memory_search)\n156: 4. Write `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md` with findings\n157: 5. Append iteration record to `deep-research-state.jsonl`\n158: 6. Let the workflow reducer update `deep-research-strategy.md`, `findings-registry.json`, and `deep-research-dashboard.md`\n159: 7. Optionally update machine-owned sections in `research/research.md` when progressive synthesis is enabled\n160: \n161: ---\n162: \n163: ## 9. TUNING GUIDE\n164: \n165: | Goal | Adjustment |\n166: |------|------------|\n167: | Deeper research | Lower convergence (0.02), raise max iterations (15) |\n168: | Faster completion | Raise convergence (0.10), lower max iterations (5) |\n169: | Broader coverage | Start with broad topic, let iterations narrow |\n170: | Specific answer | Start with specific question, lower max iterations (5) |\n171: \n172: ---\n173: \n174: ## 10. TROUBLESHOOTING\n175: \n176: | Problem | Fix |\n177: |---------|-----|\n178: | Stops too early | Lower `--convergence` from 0.05 to 0.02 |\n179: | Repeats same research | Check strategy.md \"Exhausted Approaches\" is being read |\n180: | Agent ignores state | Verify file paths in dispatch prompt |\n181: | State file corrupt | Validate JSONL: `cat research/deep-research-state.jsonl \\| jq .` |\n182: | Loop runs too long | Set lower `--max-iterations` or higher `--convergence` |\n183: \n184: ---\n185: \n186: ## 11. PROGRESS VISUALIZATION\n187: \n188: After each iteration, the orchestrator can display a text-based convergence summary:\n189: \n190: ### Format\n191: \n192: | Element | Format | Example |\n193: |---------|--------|---------|\n194: | newInfoRatio trend | ASCII sparkline | `[0.9 0.7 0.5 0.3 0.1]` |\n195: | Question coverage | Progress bar | `[=======>...] 7/10 (70%)` |\n196: | Composite score | Threshold bar | `[####----] 0.42 / 0.60` |\n197: | Noise floor | Comparison | `ratio: 0.12 > floor: 0.08` |\n198: \n199: ### Example Output\n200: \n201: ```text\n202: ITERATION 5 PROGRESS\n203: ─────────────────────\n204: newInfoRatio: 0.9 -> 0.7 -> 0.5 -> 0.3 -> 0.1  trending down\n205: Questions:   [========>..] 8/10 answered (80%)\n206: Composite:   [######--] 0.48 / 0.60 threshold\n207: Noise floor: 0.08 (ratio 0.10 ABOVE floor)\n208: Stuck count: 0 | Segment: 1 | Recovery: none\n209: Signals: RollingAvg=STOP MAD=CONTINUE Entropy=CONTINUE\n210: ```\n211: \n212: ### When to Display\n213: \n214: - After each iteration evaluation (Step 4)\n215: - In the convergence report (synthesis phase)\n216: - In confirm mode approval gates\n217: \n218: ---\n219: \n220: ## 12. RELATED\n221: \n222: | Resource | Purpose |\n223: |----------|---------|\n224: | `@context` | Single-pass codebase search (not iterative) |\n225: | `@orchestrate` | Multi-agent coordination |\n226: | `memory_context()` | Prior work retrieval |\n227: | `generate-context.js` | Supported memory save script |\n228: | `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md` | Convergence signal details |\n229: | `references/state/state_jsonl.md` | JSONL state record details |\n230: \n231: ---\n232: \n233: ## 13. REVIEW MODE\n234: \n235: Review mode has been split into a separate skill. See `deep-review/references/protocol/quick_reference.md`.\n\n(End of file - total 235 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Quick Reference\ndescription: One-page cheat sheet for the autonomous deep research loop.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep research quick reference\"\n  - \"research loop cheat sheet\"\n  - \"research iteration checklist\"\n  - \"research loop troubleshooting\"\n  - \"research tuning guide\"\n  - \"research progress visualization\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: general\nversion: 1.14.0.26\n---\n\n# Deep Research Quick Reference\n\nOne-page operator cheat sheet for the autonomous deep research loop.\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/quick_reference.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Quick Reference\ndescription: One-page cheat sheet for the autonomous deep research loop.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep research quick reference\"\n  - \"research loop cheat sheet\"\n  - \"research iteration checklist\"\n  - \"research loop troubleshooting\"\n  - \"research tuning guide\"\n  - \"research progress visualization\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: general\nversion: 1.14.0.26\n---\n\n# Deep Research Quick Reference\n\nOne-page operator cheat sheet for the autonomous deep research loop.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nLookup surface during runs covering when to invoke the loop, what each phase produces, how convergence is computed, and where live state lives on disk. Defer to the full protocol and convergence references for deep reasoning.\n\nOperator contract source of truth for this page:\n- command syntax: `.opencode/commands/deep/research.md`\n- convergence stop contract: `references/convergence/convergence.md`, `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md`, and the deep-research YAML workflow\n- state packet contract: `references/state/state_format.md`, `references/state/state_jsonl.md`, `references/state/state_outputs.md`, and `references/state/state_reducer_registry.md`\n\n---\n\n## 2. COMMANDS\n\n| Command | Description |\n|---------|-------------|\n| `/deep:research:auto \"topic\"` | Run autonomous deep research (no approval gates) |\n| `/deep:research:confirm \"topic\"` | Run with approval gates at each iteration |\n| `/deep:research \"topic\"` | Ask which mode to use |\n\n### Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Default | Description |\n|-----------|---------|-------------|\n| `--max-iterations` | 10 | Maximum loop iterations |\n| `--convergence` | 0.05 | Stop when avg newInfoRatio below this |\n| `--spec-folder` | auto | Target spec folder path |\n| `progressiveSynthesis` | true | Allow incremental `research/research.md` updates before final synthesis |\n\n---\n\n## 3. WHEN TO USE\n\n| Scenario | Use |\n|----------|-----|\n| Deep unknown topic, multi-round needed | `/deep:research` |\n| Simple question, 1-2 sources | Direct search with `@context` |\n| Check prior work only | `memory_context()` |\n| Exhaustive critical research | `/deep:research --max-iterations 15 --convergence 0.02` |\n\n---\n\n## 4. ARCHITECTURE\n\n```text\n/deep:research  -->  YAML workflow  -->  @deep-research agent (LEAF)\n    |                    |                      |\n    |                    |                      +-- Read state\n    |                    |                      +-- Research (3-5 actions)\n    |                    |                      +-- Write findings\n    |                    |                      +-- Update state\n    |                    |\n    |                    +-- Init (config, strategy, state)\n    |                    +-- Loop (dispatch, evaluate, decide)\n    |                    +-- Synthesize (final research/research.md)\n    |                    +-- Save (memory context)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. STATE FILES\n\n| File | Location | Format | Purpose |\n|------|----------|--------|---------|\n| Config | `research/deep-research-config.json` | JSON | Loop parameters |\n| State | `research/deep-research-state.jsonl` | JSONL | Iteration log (append-only) |\n| Strategy | `research/deep-research-strategy.md` | Markdown | What worked/failed, next focus |\n| Registry | `research/findings-registry.json` | JSON | Reducer-owned open/resolved questions and key findings |\n| Dashboard | `research/deep-research-dashboard.md` | Markdown | Reducer-owned lifecycle and convergence summary |\n| Iterations | `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Markdown | Per-iteration findings |\n| Output | `research/research.md` | Markdown | Workflow-owned progressive synthesis output |\n\n> **Live lifecycle branches:** `resume`, `restart`. (`fork` and `completed-continue` are deferred and not runtime-wired.) `progressiveSynthesis` defaults to `true`, so `research/research.md` is updated during the loop and finalized at synthesis.\n\n> **Path contract:** root-spec runs write directly to `{spec_folder}/research/`; child-phase and sub-phase first runs use the local `{spec_folder}/research/` directory directly, with `{ownerSlug}-pt-NN` allocated only when prior non-matching content already exists.\n\n> **Canonical pause sentinel:** `research/.deep-research-pause`\n\n> **Runtime capability matrix:** `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/capability_matrix.md` and `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/runtime_capabilities.json`\n\n---\n\n## 6. ITERATION STATUS LEGEND\n\n| Status | Meaning |\n|--------|---------|\n| `complete` | Normal iteration with findings |\n| `timeout` | Exceeded time/tool budget |\n| `error` | Failed to produce outputs |\n| `stuck` | No new information found |\n| `insight` | Low ratio but conceptual breakthrough |\n| `thought` | Analytical-only, no evidence |\n\n---\n\n## 7. CONVERGENCE DECISION TREE\n\n```text\nMax iterations reached?\n  Yes --> STOP\n\nAll questions answered?\n  Yes --> STOP\n\nstuckThreshold consecutive no-progress?\n  Yes --> STUCK_RECOVERY\n    Recovery works? --> CONTINUE\n    Recovery fails? --> STOP (with gaps)\n\nComposite convergence (3-signal weighted > 0.60)?\n  Yes --> STOP (converged)\n\nOtherwise --> CONTINUE\n```\n\n### 3-Signal Convergence Model\n\n| Signal | Weight | Min Iterations | Votes STOP When |\n|--------|--------|---------------|-----------------|\n| Rolling Average | 0.30 | 3 | avg(last 3 newInfoRatios) < convergenceThreshold |\n| MAD Noise Floor | 0.35 | 4 | latest ratio <= MAD * 1.4826 |\n| Question Entropy | 0.35 | 1 | answered / total questions >= 0.85 |\n\n**Composite stop threshold:** 0.60 -- weighted stop score must exceed this before quality guards are evaluated.\n\nQuality guards (source diversity, focus alignment, no single-weak-source) must pass before STOP.\n\n---\n\n## 8. AGENT ITERATION CHECKLIST\n\nEach @deep-research iteration:\n1. Read `deep-research-state.jsonl` and `deep-research-strategy.md`\n2. Determine focus from reducer-owned strategy \"Next Focus\"\n3. Execute 3-5 research actions (WebFetch, Grep, Read, memory_search)\n4. Write `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md` with findings\n5. Append iteration record to `deep-research-state.jsonl`\n6. Let the workflow reducer update `deep-research-strategy.md`, `findings-registry.json`, and `deep-research-dashboard.md`\n7. Optionally update machine-owned sections in `research/research.md` when progressive synthesis is enabled\n\n---\n\n## 9. TUNING GUIDE\n\n| Goal | Adjustment |\n|------|------------|\n| Deeper research | Lower convergence (0.02), raise max iterations (15) |\n| Faster completion | Raise convergence (0.10), lower max iterations (5) |\n| Broader coverage | Start with broad topic, let iterations narrow |\n| Specific answer | Start with specific question, lower max iterations (5) |\n\n---\n\n## 10. TROUBLESHOOTING\n\n| Problem | Fix |\n|---------|-----|\n| Stops too early | Lower `--convergence` from 0.05 to 0.02 |\n| Repeats same research | Check strategy.md \"Exhausted Approaches\" is being read |\n| Agent ignores state | Verify file paths in dispatch prompt |\n| State file corrupt | Validate JSONL: `cat research/deep-research-state.jsonl \\| jq .` |\n| Loop runs too long | Set lower `--max-iterations` or higher `--convergence` |\n\n---\n\n## 11. PROGRESS VISUALIZATION\n\nAfter each iteration, the orchestrator can display a text-based convergence summary:\n\n### Format\n\n| Element | Format | Example |\n|---------|--------|---------|\n| newInfoRatio trend | ASCII sparkline | `[0.9 0.7 0.5 0.3 0.1]` |\n| Question coverage | Progress bar | `[=======>...] 7/10 (70%)` |\n| Composite score | Threshold bar | `[####----] 0.42 / 0.60` |\n| Noise floor | Comparison | `ratio: 0.12 > floor: 0.08` |\n\n### Example Output\n\n```text\nITERATION 5 PROGRESS\n─────────────────────\nnewInfoRatio: 0.9 -> 0.7 -> 0.5 -> 0.3 -> 0.1  trending down\nQuestions:   [========>..] 8/10 answered (80%)\nComposite:   [######--] 0.48 / 0.60 threshold\nNoise floor: 0.08 (ratio 0.10 ABOVE floor)\nStuck count: 0 | Segment: 1 | Recovery: none\nSignals: RollingAvg=STOP MAD=CONTINUE Entropy=CONTINUE\n```\n\n### When to Display\n\n- After each iteration evaluation (Step 4)\n- In the convergence report (synthesis phase)\n- In confirm mode approval gates\n\n---\n\n## 12. RELATED\n\n| Resource | Purpose |\n|----------|---------|\n| `@context` | Single-pass codebase search (not iterative) |\n| `@orchestrate` | Multi-agent coordination |\n| `memory_context()` | Prior work retrieval |\n| `generate-context.js` | Supported memory save script |\n| `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md` | Convergence signal details |\n| `references/state/state_jsonl.md` | JSONL state record details |\n\n---\n\n## 13. REVIEW MODE\n\nReview mode has been split into a separate skill. See `deep-review/references/protocol/quick_reference.md`.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":235,"totalLines":235,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/quick_reference.md","time":{"start":1783489694557,"end":1783489694564}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0d603b1683f4755e016a4de49e7628819185e00bcdefac42ac"}},"id":"prt_f40450b21001lIgqK135upgpg4","sessionID":"ses_0bfc4afb7ffeA8X2g5OnaG20YL","messageID":"msg_f4044d0c5001HtMB4qPNkZw60i"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783489694581,"sessionID":"ses_0bfc4afb7ffeA8X2g5OnaG20YL","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_PrhmNqTSmnVAQjYOqhfJhLKU","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_outputs.md","offset":1,"limit":360},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_outputs.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Research Output Files Reference\n3: description: Markdown output structures for strategy, iterations, dashboard, synthesis, and resource-map artifacts.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"research output files\"\n6:   - \"research iteration files\"\n7:   - \"research synthesis document\"\n8:   - \"research resource map\"\n9:   - \"research strategy file\"\n10:   - \"spec anchoring output\"\n11: importance_tier: normal\n12: contextType: implementation\n13: version: 1.14.0.3\n14: ---\n15: \n16: # Deep Research Output Files Reference\n17: \n18: This reference covers human-readable packet outputs. JSONL records live in `state_jsonl.md`; reducer ownership lives in `state_reducer_registry.md`.\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n23: \n24: ### Purpose\n25: \n26: Define the human-readable deep-research packet outputs: strategy, iteration markdown, synthesis, dashboard, resource map, and bounded spec anchoring.\n27: \n28: ### When to Use\n29: \n30: Load this reference when writing or validating markdown outputs rather than JSONL records.\n31: \n32: ### Core Principle\n33: \n34: Human-readable outputs must stay synchronized with raw state and respect reducer ownership.\n35: \n36: ---\n37: \n38: ## 2. STRATEGY FILE\n39: \n40: `deep-research-strategy.md` is the persistent research plan. The reducer owns machine-managed sections.\n41: \n42: Required sections:\n43: \n44: - Research Topic\n45: - Known Context\n46: - Key Questions\n47: - Answered Questions\n48: - What Worked\n49: - What Failed\n50: - Exhausted Approaches\n51: - Ruled-Out Directions\n52: - Next Focus\n53: \n54: Update protocol:\n55: \n56: - read strategy before each iteration;\n57: - choose one focus from `Next Focus`;\n58: - append what worked, failed, and was ruled out;\n59: - update answered/open questions through reducer-owned sections;\n60: - when a STOP candidate is blocked, override `Next Focus` with the blocker recovery focus.\n61: \n62: ---\n63: \n64: ## 3. ITERATION FILES\n65: \n66: Iteration files are write-once markdown narratives.\n67: \n68: ```text\n69: research/iterations/iteration-001.md\n70: research/iterations/iteration-002.md\n71: research/iterations/iteration-003.md\n72: ```\n73: \n74: Required shape:\n75: \n76: | Markdown Element | Required Content |\n77: |------------------|------------------|\n78: | H1 title | `Iteration N: Focus Area` |\n79: | `Focus` section | What this iteration investigated |\n80: | `Findings` section | Evidence-backed findings with source citations |\n81: | `Sources Consulted` section | Files, URLs, memory hits, or commands used |\n82: | `Assessment` section | `newInfoRatio`, novelty justification, and confidence notes |\n83: | `Reflection` section | What worked, failed, or was ruled out |\n84: | `Recommended Next Focus` section | One concrete next focus |\n85: \n86: Every finding must cite a source such as `[SOURCE: file:path:line]` or `[SOURCE: https://example.test]`.\n87: \n88: ---\n89: \n90: ## 4. RESEARCH SYNTHESIS\n91: \n92: `research.md` is the workflow-owned synthesis output at `{artifact_dir}/research.md`.\n93: \n94: Rules:\n95: \n96: - progressive synthesis may update the file during the loop;\n97: - final synthesis consolidates duplicate findings and unresolved gaps;\n98: - prior findings are not silently overwritten;\n99: - generated or machine-owned sections must be marked explicitly when the workflow uses them;\n100: - when `resource_map_present` is true, cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in References.\n101: \n102: ---\n103: \n104: ## 5. DASHBOARD\n105: \n106: `deep-research-dashboard.md` is auto-generated from JSONL, strategy, and registry state.\n107: \n108: Expected sections:\n109: \n110: | Section | Source |\n111: |---------|--------|\n112: | Iteration Table | JSONL iteration records |\n113: | Question Status | Strategy + registry |\n114: | Convergence Trend | `convergenceSignals` + reducer |\n115: | Dead Ends | JSONL `ruledOut` + strategy |\n116: | Blocked Stops | Registry blocked-stop history |\n117: | Graph Convergence | Graph convergence registry fields |\n118: | Next Focus | Strategy |\n119: \n120: Generation rules:\n121: \n122: - regenerate after each iteration evaluation;\n123: - compute derived values from raw state;\n124: - overwrite the full dashboard rather than appending;\n125: - if state is missing, write a minimal \"No iteration data available\" dashboard;\n126: - agent writes are discarded on next refresh.\n127: \n128: ---\n129: \n130: ## 6. RESOURCE MAP\n131: \n132: When `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init:\n133: \n134: - persist `resource_map_present: true` in config;\n135: - summarize section counts and themes into strategy `Known Context`;\n136: - treat listed files as known inventory, not net-new discoveries;\n137: - cite the map in final synthesis references;\n138: - emit `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md` from converged deltas unless disabled.\n139: \n140: When absent:\n141: \n142: - persist `resource_map_present: false`;\n143: - write `resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate` into `Known Context`;\n144: - continue normally.\n145: \n146: ---\n147: \n148: ## 7. SPEC ANCHORING OUTPUT\n149: \n150: `references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md` defines bounded `spec.md` writes:\n151: \n152: - acquire `research/.deep-research.lock`;\n153: - classify `folder_state`;\n154: - seed or append bounded context during init when allowed;\n155: - replace exactly one generated findings fence during synthesis.\n156: \n157: This output path is protocol-owned, not iteration-agent owned.\n\n(End of file - total 157 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Output Files Reference\ndescription: Markdown output structures for strategy, iterations, dashboard, synthesis, and resource-map artifacts.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research output files\"\n  - \"research iteration files\"\n  - \"research synthesis document\"\n  - \"research resource map\"\n  - \"research strategy file\"\n  - \"spec anchoring output\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.3\n---\n\n# Deep Research Output Files Reference\n\nThis reference covers human-readable packet outputs. JSONL records live in `state_jsonl.md`; reducer ownership lives in `state_reducer_registry.md`.\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_outputs.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Output Files Reference\ndescription: Markdown output structures for strategy, iterations, dashboard, synthesis, and resource-map artifacts.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research output files\"\n  - \"research iteration files\"\n  - \"research synthesis document\"\n  - \"research resource map\"\n  - \"research strategy file\"\n  - \"spec anchoring output\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.3\n---\n\n# Deep Research Output Files Reference\n\nThis reference covers human-readable packet outputs. JSONL records live in `state_jsonl.md`; reducer ownership lives in `state_reducer_registry.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nDefine the human-readable deep-research packet outputs: strategy, iteration markdown, synthesis, dashboard, resource map, and bounded spec anchoring.\n\n### When to Use\n\nLoad this reference when writing or validating markdown outputs rather than JSONL records.\n\n### Core Principle\n\nHuman-readable outputs must stay synchronized with raw state and respect reducer ownership.\n\n---\n\n## 2. STRATEGY FILE\n\n`deep-research-strategy.md` is the persistent research plan. The reducer owns machine-managed sections.\n\nRequired sections:\n\n- Research Topic\n- Known Context\n- Key Questions\n- Answered Questions\n- What Worked\n- What Failed\n- Exhausted Approaches\n- Ruled-Out Directions\n- Next Focus\n\nUpdate protocol:\n\n- read strategy before each iteration;\n- choose one focus from `Next Focus`;\n- append what worked, failed, and was ruled out;\n- update answered/open questions through reducer-owned sections;\n- when a STOP candidate is blocked, override `Next Focus` with the blocker recovery focus.\n\n---\n\n## 3. ITERATION FILES\n\nIteration files are write-once markdown narratives.\n\n```text\nresearch/iterations/iteration-001.md\nresearch/iterations/iteration-002.md\nresearch/iterations/iteration-003.md\n```\n\nRequired shape:\n\n| Markdown Element | Required Content |\n|------------------|------------------|\n| H1 title | `Iteration N: Focus Area` |\n| `Focus` section | What this iteration investigated |\n| `Findings` section | Evidence-backed findings with source citations |\n| `Sources Consulted` section | Files, URLs, memory hits, or commands used |\n| `Assessment` section | `newInfoRatio`, novelty justification, and confidence notes |\n| `Reflection` section | What worked, failed, or was ruled out |\n| `Recommended Next Focus` section | One concrete next focus |\n\nEvery finding must cite a source such as `[SOURCE: file:path:line]` or `[SOURCE: https://example.test]`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. RESEARCH SYNTHESIS\n\n`research.md` is the workflow-owned synthesis output at `{artifact_dir}/research.md`.\n\nRules:\n\n- progressive synthesis may update the file during the loop;\n- final synthesis consolidates duplicate findings and unresolved gaps;\n- prior findings are not silently overwritten;\n- generated or machine-owned sections must be marked explicitly when the workflow uses them;\n- when `resource_map_present` is true, cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in References.\n\n---\n\n## 5. DASHBOARD\n\n`deep-research-dashboard.md` is auto-generated from JSONL, strategy, and registry state.\n\nExpected sections:\n\n| Section | Source |\n|---------|--------|\n| Iteration Table | JSONL iteration records |\n| Question Status | Strategy + registry |\n| Convergence Trend | `convergenceSignals` + reducer |\n| Dead Ends | JSONL `ruledOut` + strategy |\n| Blocked Stops | Registry blocked-stop history |\n| Graph Convergence | Graph convergence registry fields |\n| Next Focus | Strategy |\n\nGeneration rules:\n\n- regenerate after each iteration evaluation;\n- compute derived values from raw state;\n- overwrite the full dashboard rather than appending;\n- if state is missing, write a minimal \"No iteration data available\" dashboard;\n- agent writes are discarded on next refresh.\n\n---\n\n## 6. RESOURCE MAP\n\nWhen `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init:\n\n- persist `resource_map_present: true` in config;\n- summarize section counts and themes into strategy `Known Context`;\n- treat listed files as known inventory, not net-new discoveries;\n- cite the map in final synthesis references;\n- emit `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md` from converged deltas unless disabled.\n\nWhen absent:\n\n- persist `resource_map_present: false`;\n- write `resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate` into `Known Context`;\n- continue normally.\n\n---\n\n## 7. SPEC ANCHORING OUTPUT\n\n`references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md` defines bounded `spec.md` writes:\n\n- acquire `research/.deep-research.lock`;\n- classify `folder_state`;\n- seed or append bounded context during init when allowed;\n- replace exactly one generated findings fence during synthesis.\n\nThis output path is protocol-owned, not iteration-agent owned.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":157,"totalLines":157,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_outputs.md","time":{"start":1783489694577,"end":1783489694581}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0d603b1683f4755e016a4de49e76388191b57169d49ba0762f"}},"id":"prt_f40450b5f0016bnKRwrHZ5JiQY","sessionID":"ses_0bfc4afb7ffeA8X2g5OnaG20YL","messageID":"msg_f4044d0c5001HtMB4qPNkZw60i"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783489694591,"sessionID":"ses_0bfc4afb7ffeA8X2g5OnaG20YL","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_5HJTFZDi0UZYaUoc3NRmaneM","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_jsonl.md","offset":1,"limit":300},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_jsonl.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Research JSONL State Reference\n3: description: Config, iteration, event, lineage, graph, and blocked-stop records for deep-research state logs.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"research state jsonl\"\n6:   - \"research config record\"\n7:   - \"research iteration records\"\n8:   - \"research negative knowledge\"\n9:   - \"research graph events\"\n10:   - \"research event records\"\n11: importance_tier: normal\n12: contextType: implementation\n13: version: 1.14.0.3\n14: ---\n15: \n16: # Deep Research JSONL State Reference\n17: \n18: `deep-research-state.jsonl` is append-only. Each line is one JSON object. The first line is normally the config record, followed by iteration and event records.\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n23: \n24: ### Purpose\n25: \n26: Define the append-only JSONL records used by deep-research config, iteration, lifecycle, graph, pause, stuck-recovery, and blocked-stop state.\n27: \n28: ### When to Use\n29: \n30: Load this reference when validating state logs, adding event records, reconstructing a packet, or mapping legacy stop labels to current values.\n31: \n32: ### Core Principle\n33: \n34: Raw JSONL is append-only evidence. Reducer-owned files derive from it, but they do not replace it.\n35: \n36: ---\n37: \n38: ## 2. CONFIG RECORD\n39: \n40: The config record captures the initialized loop contract.\n41: \n42: ```json\n43: {\n44:   \"type\": \"config\",\n45:   \"topic\": \"API response time optimization\",\n46:   \"maxIterations\": 10,\n47:   \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.05,\n48:   \"stuckThreshold\": 3,\n49:   \"specFolder\": \"028-auto-deep-research\",\n50:   \"createdAt\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n51: }\n52: ```\n53: \n54: The full config file also stores executor, lineage, reducer, capability matrix, pause sentinel, archive, and file-protection settings.\n55: \n56: ---\n57: \n58: ## 3. ITERATION RECORDS\n59: \n60: ```json\n61: {\n62:   \"type\": \"iteration\",\n63:   \"run\": 1,\n64:   \"status\": \"complete\",\n65:   \"focus\": \"Initial broad survey\",\n66:   \"findingsCount\": 5,\n67:   \"newInfoRatio\": 1.0,\n68:   \"noveltyJustification\": \"First pass; all findings are new to this packet\",\n69:   \"keyQuestions\": [\"What causes latency?\"],\n70:   \"answeredQuestions\": [\"What causes latency?\"],\n71:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:05:00Z\",\n72:   \"durationMs\": 45000\n73: }\n74: ```\n75: \n76: | Field | Required | Notes |\n77: |-------|----------|-------|\n78: | `type` | Yes | `iteration` |\n79: | `run` | Yes | 1-indexed iteration number |\n80: | `status` | Yes | See status values below |\n81: | `focus` | Yes | Single focus investigated |\n82: | `findingsCount` | Yes | Number of findings reported |\n83: | `newInfoRatio` | Yes | Novelty score used by convergence |\n84: | `noveltyJustification` | Recommended | One-sentence explanation of the ratio |\n85: | `keyQuestions` | Recommended | Questions considered during this iteration |\n86: | `answeredQuestions` | Recommended | Questions answered by evidence |\n87: | `ruledOut` | Optional | Negative knowledge entries |\n88: | `graphEvents` | Optional | Coverage graph mutations |\n89: \n90: Status values:\n91: \n92: | Status | Meaning |\n93: |--------|---------|\n94: | `complete` | Normal evidence-gathering iteration |\n95: | `timeout` | Time/tool budget exceeded |\n96: | `error` | Tool, parse, or unexpected failure |\n97: | `stuck` | No new information and no clear next direction |\n98: | `insight` | Low ratio but important conceptual breakthrough |\n99: | `thought` | Analytical-only iteration; excluded from stuck and signal math |\n100: \n101: ---\n102: \n103: ## 4. CONVERGENCE SIGNAL FIELDS\n104: \n105: When the composite algorithm runs, the iteration may include signal values:\n106: \n107: ```json\n108: {\n109:   \"type\": \"iteration\",\n110:   \"run\": 5,\n111:   \"convergenceSignals\": {\n112:     \"rollingAvg\": 0.12,\n113:     \"madScore\": 0.08,\n114:     \"entropyCoverage\": 0.71,\n115:     \"compositeStop\": 0.42\n116:   }\n117: }\n118: ```\n119: \n120: Signal rules live in `../convergence/convergence_signals.md`.\n121: \n122: ---\n123: \n124: ## 5. NEGATIVE KNOWLEDGE\n125: \n126: Use `ruledOut` to preserve eliminated approaches.\n127: \n128: ```json\n129: {\n130:   \"type\": \"iteration\",\n131:   \"run\": 3,\n132:   \"status\": \"complete\",\n133:   \"ruledOut\": [\n134:     {\n135:       \"approach\": \"HTTP/3 multiplexing\",\n136:       \"reason\": \"No server-side support in target environment\",\n137:       \"evidence\": \"file:docs/protocols.md:42\"\n138:     }\n139:   ]\n140: }\n141: ```\n142: \n143: Ruled-out directions should also appear in strategy and synthesis outputs.\n144: \n145: ---\n146: \n147: ## 6. GRAPH EVENTS\n148: \n149: `graphEvents` records coverage graph mutations from an iteration.\n150: \n151: ```json\n152: {\n153:   \"type\": \"iteration\",\n154:   \"run\": 4,\n155:   \"graphEvents\": [\n156:     {\"type\": \"question\", \"id\": \"q-reconnect\", \"label\": \"How should reconnect work?\"},\n157:     {\"type\": \"finding\", \"id\": \"f-backoff\", \"label\": \"Exponential backoff is required\"},\n158:     {\"type\": \"edge\", \"from\": \"f-backoff\", \"to\": \"q-reconnect\", \"relation\": \"ANSWERS\"}\n159:   ]\n160: }\n161: ```\n162: \n163: Valid node types are `question`, `finding`, `claim`, and `source`; `edge` records connect nodes. IDs must be unique within a single `(specFolder, loopType, sessionId)` namespace. Reusing the same logical ID across independent sessions is allowed because the coverage graph uses a composite key.\n164: \n165: ---\n166: \n167: ## 7. EVENT RECORDS\n168: \n169: Lifecycle event:\n170: \n171: ```json\n172: {\n173:   \"type\": \"event\",\n174:   \"event\": \"resumed\",\n175:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n176:   \"sessionId\": \"dr-2026-05-24T00-00-00Z\",\n177:   \"parentSessionId\": \"dr-2026-05-24T00-00-00Z\",\n178:   \"lineageMode\": \"resume\",\n179:   \"continuedFromRun\": 4,\n180:   \"generation\": 1,\n181:   \"archivedPath\": null,\n182:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n183: }\n184: ```\n185: \n186: Blocked stop event:\n187: \n188: ```json\n189: {\n190:   \"type\": \"event\",\n191:   \"event\": \"blocked_stop\",\n192:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n193:   \"run\": 7,\n194:   \"stopReason\": \"blockedStop\",\n195:   \"blockedBy\": [\"keyQuestionCoverage\", \"sourceDiversity\"],\n196:   \"recoveryStrategy\": \"focus_pivot\",\n197:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n198: }\n199: ```\n200: \n201: Pause event:\n202: \n203: ```json\n204: {\n205:   \"type\": \"event\",\n206:   \"event\": \"userPaused\",\n207:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n208:   \"run\": 7,\n209:   \"stopReason\": \"userPaused\",\n210:   \"sentinelPath\": \"research/.deep-research-pause\",\n211:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n212: }\n213: ```\n214: \n215: Stuck recovery event:\n216: \n217: ```json\n218: {\n219:   \"type\": \"event\",\n220:   \"event\": \"stuckRecovery\",\n221:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n222:   \"run\": 7,\n223:   \"stopReason\": \"stuckRecovery\",\n224:   \"fromFocus\": \"Connection pooling\",\n225:   \"toFocus\": \"Transport alternatives\",\n226:   \"strategy\": \"try_opposites\",\n227:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n228: }\n229: ```\n230: \n231: Idea observation event:\n232: \n233: ```json\n234: {\n235:   \"type\": \"event\",\n236:   \"event\": \"idea_observed\",\n237:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n238:   \"run\": 7,\n239:   \"ideaId\": \"idea-cache-stampede\",\n240:   \"idea\": \"Investigate cache stampede mitigation as a follow-up focus\",\n241:   \"category\": \"ideas\",\n242:   \"source\": \"iteration-007.md\",\n243:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n244: }\n245: ```\n246: \n247: Leaf agents may append `idea_observed` for promising tangents. They must not append `idea_promoted`; promotion is reducer-owned.\n248: \n249: Idea promotion event:\n250: \n251: ```json\n252: {\n253:   \"type\": \"event\",\n254:   \"event\": \"idea_promoted\",\n255:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n256:   \"run\": 8,\n257:   \"ideaId\": \"idea-cache-stampede\",\n258:   \"idea\": \"Investigate cache stampede mitigation as a follow-up focus\",\n259:   \"category\": \"ideas\",\n260:   \"observationCount\": 2,\n261:   \"minIdeaObservations\": 2,\n262:   \"firstObservedRun\": 6,\n263:   \"lastObservedRun\": 7,\n264:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:02:00Z\"\n265: }\n266: ```\n267: \n268: The reducer emits `idea_promoted` once per idea after replay shows `observationCount >= minIdeaObservations`. `minIdeaObservations` defaults to `2` and is clamped to the inclusive range `1..10`.\n269: \n270: Rejected idea event:\n271: \n272: ```json\n273: {\n274:   \"type\": \"event\",\n275:   \"event\": \"idea_rejected\",\n276:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n277:   \"run\": 7,\n278:   \"ideaId\": \"idea-cache-stampede\",\n279:   \"idea\": \"Investigate cache stampede mitigation as a follow-up focus\",\n280:   \"category\": \"ideas\",\n281:   \"reason\": \"Already rejected by environment evidence\",\n282:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n283: }\n284: ```\n285: \n286: `idea_rejected` durably suppresses the matching promoted idea and also enters the reducer-owned rejected-pattern cache. Use `category: \"general\"` only when the rejection should suppress matching text across next-focus, recovery, and ideas candidates.\n287: \n288: Rejected idea removal event:\n289: \n290: ```json\n291: {\n292:   \"type\": \"event\",\n293:   \"event\": \"ideaRejectedRemoved\",\n294:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n295:   \"pattern\": \"Retry HTTP/3 as the primary latency fix\",\n296:   \"category\": \"next-focus\",\n297:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n298: }\n299: ```\n300: \n\n(Showing lines 1-300 of 325. Use offset=301 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Research JSONL State Reference\ndescription: Config, iteration, event, lineage, graph, and blocked-stop records for deep-research state logs.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research state jsonl\"\n  - \"research config record\"\n  - \"research iteration records\"\n  - \"research negative knowledge\"\n  - \"research graph events\"\n  - \"research event records\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.3\n---\n\n# Deep Research JSONL State Reference\n\n`deep-research-state.jsonl` is append-only. Each line is one JSON object. The first line is normally the config record, followed by iteration and event records.\n\n---","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_jsonl.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Research JSONL State Reference\ndescription: Config, iteration, event, lineage, graph, and blocked-stop records for deep-research state logs.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research state jsonl\"\n  - \"research config record\"\n  - \"research iteration records\"\n  - \"research negative knowledge\"\n  - \"research graph events\"\n  - \"research event records\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.3\n---\n\n# Deep Research JSONL State Reference\n\n`deep-research-state.jsonl` is append-only. Each line is one JSON object. The first line is normally the config record, followed by iteration and event records.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nDefine the append-only JSONL records used by deep-research config, iteration, lifecycle, graph, pause, stuck-recovery, and blocked-stop state.\n\n### When to Use\n\nLoad this reference when validating state logs, adding event records, reconstructing a packet, or mapping legacy stop labels to current values.\n\n### Core Principle\n\nRaw JSONL is append-only evidence. Reducer-owned files derive from it, but they do not replace it.\n\n---\n\n## 2. CONFIG RECORD\n\nThe config record captures the initialized loop contract.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"config\",\n  \"topic\": \"API response time optimization\",\n  \"maxIterations\": 10,\n  \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.05,\n  \"stuckThreshold\": 3,\n  \"specFolder\": \"028-auto-deep-research\",\n  \"createdAt\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nThe full config file also stores executor, lineage, reducer, capability matrix, pause sentinel, archive, and file-protection settings.\n\n---\n\n## 3. ITERATION RECORDS\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"iteration\",\n  \"run\": 1,\n  \"status\": \"complete\",\n  \"focus\": \"Initial broad survey\",\n  \"findingsCount\": 5,\n  \"newInfoRatio\": 1.0,\n  \"noveltyJustification\": \"First pass; all findings are new to this packet\",\n  \"keyQuestions\": [\"What causes latency?\"],\n  \"answeredQuestions\": [\"What causes latency?\"],\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:05:00Z\",\n  \"durationMs\": 45000\n}\n```\n\n| Field | Required | Notes |\n|-------|----------|-------|\n| `type` | Yes | `iteration` |\n| `run` | Yes | 1-indexed iteration number |\n| `status` | Yes | See status values below |\n| `focus` | Yes | Single focus investigated |\n| `findingsCount` | Yes | Number of findings reported |\n| `newInfoRatio` | Yes | Novelty score used by convergence |\n| `noveltyJustification` | Recommended | One-sentence explanation of the ratio |\n| `keyQuestions` | Recommended | Questions considered during this iteration |\n| `answeredQuestions` | Recommended | Questions answered by evidence |\n| `ruledOut` | Optional | Negative knowledge entries |\n| `graphEvents` | Optional | Coverage graph mutations |\n\nStatus values:\n\n| Status | Meaning |\n|--------|---------|\n| `complete` | Normal evidence-gathering iteration |\n| `timeout` | Time/tool budget exceeded |\n| `error` | Tool, parse, or unexpected failure |\n| `stuck` | No new information and no clear next direction |\n| `insight` | Low ratio but important conceptual breakthrough |\n| `thought` | Analytical-only iteration; excluded from stuck and signal math |\n\n---\n\n## 4. CONVERGENCE SIGNAL FIELDS\n\nWhen the composite algorithm runs, the iteration may include signal values:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"iteration\",\n  \"run\": 5,\n  \"convergenceSignals\": {\n    \"rollingAvg\": 0.12,\n    \"madScore\": 0.08,\n    \"entropyCoverage\": 0.71,\n    \"compositeStop\": 0.42\n  }\n}\n```\n\nSignal rules live in `../convergence/convergence_signals.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. NEGATIVE KNOWLEDGE\n\nUse `ruledOut` to preserve eliminated approaches.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"iteration\",\n  \"run\": 3,\n  \"status\": \"complete\",\n  \"ruledOut\": [\n    {\n      \"approach\": \"HTTP/3 multiplexing\",\n      \"reason\": \"No server-side support in target environment\",\n      \"evidence\": \"file:docs/protocols.md:42\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nRuled-out directions should also appear in strategy and synthesis outputs.\n\n---\n\n## 6. GRAPH EVENTS\n\n`graphEvents` records coverage graph mutations from an iteration.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"iteration\",\n  \"run\": 4,\n  \"graphEvents\": [\n    {\"type\": \"question\", \"id\": \"q-reconnect\", \"label\": \"How should reconnect work?\"},\n    {\"type\": \"finding\", \"id\": \"f-backoff\", \"label\": \"Exponential backoff is required\"},\n    {\"type\": \"edge\", \"from\": \"f-backoff\", \"to\": \"q-reconnect\", \"relation\": \"ANSWERS\"}\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nValid node types are `question`, `finding`, `claim`, and `source`; `edge` records connect nodes. IDs must be unique within a single `(specFolder, loopType, sessionId)` namespace. Reusing the same logical ID across independent sessions is allowed because the coverage graph uses a composite key.\n\n---\n\n## 7. EVENT RECORDS\n\nLifecycle event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"resumed\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"sessionId\": \"dr-2026-05-24T00-00-00Z\",\n  \"parentSessionId\": \"dr-2026-05-24T00-00-00Z\",\n  \"lineageMode\": \"resume\",\n  \"continuedFromRun\": 4,\n  \"generation\": 1,\n  \"archivedPath\": null,\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nBlocked stop event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"blocked_stop\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"run\": 7,\n  \"stopReason\": \"blockedStop\",\n  \"blockedBy\": [\"keyQuestionCoverage\", \"sourceDiversity\"],\n  \"recoveryStrategy\": \"focus_pivot\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nPause event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"userPaused\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"run\": 7,\n  \"stopReason\": \"userPaused\",\n  \"sentinelPath\": \"research/.deep-research-pause\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nStuck recovery event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"stuckRecovery\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"run\": 7,\n  \"stopReason\": \"stuckRecovery\",\n  \"fromFocus\": \"Connection pooling\",\n  \"toFocus\": \"Transport alternatives\",\n  \"strategy\": \"try_opposites\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nIdea observation event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"idea_observed\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"run\": 7,\n  \"ideaId\": \"idea-cache-stampede\",\n  \"idea\": \"Investigate cache stampede mitigation as a follow-up focus\",\n  \"category\": \"ideas\",\n  \"source\": \"iteration-007.md\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nLeaf agents may append `idea_observed` for promising tangents. They must not append `idea_promoted`; promotion is reducer-owned.\n\nIdea promotion event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"idea_promoted\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"run\": 8,\n  \"ideaId\": \"idea-cache-stampede\",\n  \"idea\": \"Investigate cache stampede mitigation as a follow-up focus\",\n  \"category\": \"ideas\",\n  \"observationCount\": 2,\n  \"minIdeaObservations\": 2,\n  \"firstObservedRun\": 6,\n  \"lastObservedRun\": 7,\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:02:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nThe reducer emits `idea_promoted` once per idea after replay shows `observationCount >= minIdeaObservations`. `minIdeaObservations` defaults to `2` and is clamped to the inclusive range `1..10`.\n\nRejected idea event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"idea_rejected\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"run\": 7,\n  \"ideaId\": \"idea-cache-stampede\",\n  \"idea\": \"Investigate cache stampede mitigation as a follow-up focus\",\n  \"category\": \"ideas\",\n  \"reason\": \"Already rejected by environment evidence\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\n`idea_rejected` durably suppresses the matching promoted idea and also enters the reducer-owned rejected-pattern cache. Use `category: \"general\"` only when the rejection should suppress matching text across next-focus, recovery, and ideas candidates.\n\nRejected idea removal event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"ideaRejectedRemoved\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"pattern\": \"Retry HTTP/3 as the primary latency fix\",\n  \"category\": \"next-focus\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":300,"totalLines":325,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_jsonl.md","time":{"start":1783489694587,"end":1783489694590}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0d603b1683f4755e016a4de49e76408191a60049e82fb9c163"}},"id":"prt_f40450b72001MpC5Sf0fJmS7i6","sessionID":"ses_0bfc4afb7ffeA8X2g5OnaG20YL","messageID":"msg_f4044d0c5001HtMB4qPNkZw60i"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783489694624,"sessionID":"ses_0bfc4afb7ffeA8X2g5OnaG20YL","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_7oszHYoSLiBbumjA0CnSkkFn","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/verify-iteration.cjs","offset":1,"limit":260},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/verify-iteration.cjs</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: #!/usr/bin/env node\n2: 'use strict';\n3: \n4: // After-dispatch leaf-reliability check for the deep-loop iteration loop.\n5: //\n6: // A dispatched leaf owes THREE artifacts per iteration: the narrative markdown\n7: // (iterations/iteration-NNN.md), an appended canonical state-log record, and a\n8: // per-iteration delta file. The state-log record must also carry route-proof\n9: // fields proving the leaf ran as itself (mode, target_agent, agent_definition_loaded,\n10: // resolved_route). A model-driven loop is trusted to self-check today, which lets a\n11: // silently-incomplete leaf advance the loop. This makes the check mechanical: exit\n12: // non-zero with a single machine reason so the workflow can re-dispatch the same\n13: // iteration once before recording an error and continuing.\n14: \n15: const fs = require('node:fs');\n16: const path = require('node:path');\n17: \n18: const LEAF_BY_LOOP = {\n19:   review: 'deep-review',\n20:   research: 'deep-research',\n21: };\n22: \n23: const STATE_LOG_BY_LOOP = {\n24:   review: 'deep-review-state.jsonl',\n25:   research: 'deep-research-state.jsonl',\n26: };\n27: \n28: const REASONS = {\n29:   ITERATION_FILE_MISSING: 'iteration_file_missing',\n30:   ITERATION_VERDICT_MISSING: 'iteration_verdict_missing',\n31:   STATE_RECORD_MISSING: 'state_record_missing',\n32:   ROUTE_PROOF_MISSING: 'route_proof_missing',\n33:   ROUTE_PROOF_MISMATCH: 'route_proof_mismatch',\n34:   DELTA_FILE_MISSING: 'delta_file_missing',\n35: };\n36: \n37: function pad3(n) {\n38:   return String(n).padStart(3, '0');\n39: }\n40: \n41: function parseArgs(argv) {\n42:   const out = { json: false };\n43:   for (let i = 0; i < argv.length; i += 1) {\n44:     const a = argv[i];\n45:     if (a === '--loop-type') { out.loopType = argv[i + 1]; i += 1; }\n46:     else if (a === '--artifact-dir') { out.artifactDir = argv[i + 1]; i += 1; }\n47:     else if (a === '--iteration') { out.iteration = parseInt(argv[i + 1], 10); i += 1; }\n48:     else if (a === '--json') { out.json = true; }\n49:     else if (a === '--help' || a === '-h') { out.help = true; }\n50:     else { out.error = `unknown flag: ${a}`; }\n51:   }\n52:   return out;\n53: }\n54: \n55: // Read a JSONL file and return parsed objects, skipping blank/malformed lines so a\n56: // single corrupt append never crashes the gate.\n57: function readJsonlRecords(filePath) {\n58:   let raw;\n59:   try {\n60:     raw = fs.readFileSync(filePath, 'utf8');\n61:   } catch (_) {\n62:     return null; // file absent/unreadable\n63:   }\n64:   const records = [];\n65:   for (const line of raw.split('\\n')) {\n66:     const trimmed = line.trim();\n67:     if (!trimmed) continue;\n68:     try {\n69:       records.push(JSON.parse(trimmed));\n70:     } catch (_) {\n71:       // skip malformed line\n72:     }\n73:   }\n74:   return records;\n75: }\n76: \n77: // The narrative file is written as iteration-NNN.md but the leaf may append a\n78: // descriptive suffix (iteration-NNN-some-focus.md), so match the padded number as a\n79: // prefix bounded by \".\" or \"-\" to avoid confusing 002 with 020.\n80: function findIterationNarrative(iterationsDir, iteration) {\n81:   const nnn = pad3(iteration);\n82:   let entries;\n83:   try {\n84:     entries = fs.readdirSync(iterationsDir);\n85:   } catch (_) {\n86:     return null;\n87:   }\n88:   const re = new RegExp(`^iteration-${nnn}(?:\\\\.md$|-.*\\\\.md$)`);\n89:   for (const name of entries) {\n90:     if (re.test(name)) return path.join(iterationsDir, name);\n91:   }\n92:   return null;\n93: }\n94: \n95: function isNonEmptyString(value) {\n96:   return typeof value === 'string' && value.trim().length > 0;\n97: }\n98: \n99: // Route-proof lives on the canonical iteration record. Absent fields => the leaf did\n100: // not emit route-proof at all; present-but-wrong => it ran as something other than\n101: // its own leaf identity or in the wrong mode.\n102: function checkRouteProof(record, loopType, leaf) {\n103:   const hasMode = 'mode' in record;\n104:   const hasTarget = 'target_agent' in record;\n105:   const hasLoaded = 'agent_definition_loaded' in record;\n106:   const hasRoute = 'resolved_route' in record;\n107:   if (!hasMode || !hasTarget || !hasLoaded || !hasRoute) {\n108:     return REASONS.ROUTE_PROOF_MISSING;\n109:   }\n110:   if (\n111:     record.mode !== loopType ||\n112:     record.target_agent !== leaf ||\n113:     record.agent_definition_loaded !== true ||\n114:     !isNonEmptyString(record.resolved_route)\n115:   ) {\n116:     return REASONS.ROUTE_PROOF_MISMATCH;\n117:   }\n118:   return null;\n119: }\n120: \n121: function verify(loopType, artifactDir, iteration) {\n122:   const leaf = LEAF_BY_LOOP[loopType];\n123:   const stateLogName = STATE_LOG_BY_LOOP[loopType];\n124: \n125:   // 1. Iteration narrative markdown.\n126:   const narrativePath = findIterationNarrative(path.join(artifactDir, 'iterations'), iteration);\n127:   if (!narrativePath) {\n128:     return { ok: false, reason: REASONS.ITERATION_FILE_MISSING, detail: `no iterations/iteration-${pad3(iteration)}*.md under ${artifactDir}` };\n129:   }\n130:   const narrative = fs.readFileSync(narrativePath, 'utf8');\n131:   if (!narrative.trim()) {\n132:     return { ok: false, reason: REASONS.ITERATION_FILE_MISSING, detail: `${narrativePath} is empty` };\n133:   }\n134:   // Review narratives must end on a machine-readable verdict; research/context use a\n135:   // different closing shape, so only review enforces the verdict line here.\n136:   if (loopType === 'review' && !/Review verdict:\\s*(PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL)/i.test(narrative)) {\n137:     return { ok: false, reason: REASONS.ITERATION_VERDICT_MISSING, detail: `${narrativePath} lacks a \"Review verdict: PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL\" line` };\n138:   }\n139: \n140:   // 2. Canonical state-log record for this iteration + route-proof.\n141:   const stateRecords = readJsonlRecords(path.join(artifactDir, stateLogName));\n142:   // Review/research key the iteration number as `iteration`; context keys it as `run`.\n143:   // Match either so one shim covers all three modes (a non-numeric run-id yields NaN\n144:   // and never false-matches). Take the LAST matching record, not the first: the state\n145:   // log is append-only, so a re-dispatched iteration appends a corrected record after\n146:   // the bad one -- matching the first would keep reporting the stale failure and defeat\n147:   // the bounded retry. The state reducer applies the same latest-record-wins rule.\n148:   const iterationRecord = (stateRecords || []).findLast(\n149:     (r) => r && r.type === 'iteration' && (Number(r.iteration) === iteration || Number(r.run) === iteration),\n150:   );\n151:   if (!iterationRecord) {\n152:     return { ok: false, reason: REASONS.STATE_RECORD_MISSING, detail: `no type=iteration record with iteration=${iteration} in ${stateLogName}` };\n153:   }\n154:   const routeReason = checkRouteProof(iterationRecord, loopType, leaf);\n155:   if (routeReason) {\n156:     return { ok: false, reason: routeReason, detail: `iteration ${iteration} state record failed route-proof (expected mode=${loopType} target_agent=${leaf})` };\n157:   }\n158: \n159:   // 3. Per-iteration delta file with at least one iteration record.\n160:   const deltaRecords = readJsonlRecords(path.join(artifactDir, 'deltas', `iter-${pad3(iteration)}.jsonl`));\n161:   if (!deltaRecords || !deltaRecords.some((r) => r && r.type === 'iteration')) {\n162:     return { ok: false, reason: REASONS.DELTA_FILE_MISSING, detail: `deltas/iter-${pad3(iteration)}.jsonl missing or has no type=iteration record` };\n163:   }\n164: \n165:   return { ok: true, reason: null, detail: `iteration ${iteration} complete: narrative + route-proof + delta` };\n166: }\n167: \n168: function main(argv = process.argv.slice(2)) {\n169:   const args = parseArgs(argv);\n170:   if (args.help) {\n171:     process.stdout.write('Usage: verify-iteration.cjs --loop-type review|research|context --artifact-dir <dir> --iteration <N> [--json]\\n');\n172:     return 0;\n173:   }\n174:   if (args.error) { process.stderr.write(`${args.error}\\n`); return 2; }\n175:   if (!args.loopType || !LEAF_BY_LOOP[args.loopType]) { process.stderr.write('--loop-type must be one of review|research\\n'); return 2; }\n176:   if (!args.artifactDir) { process.stderr.write('--artifact-dir is required\\n'); return 2; }\n177:   if (!Number.isInteger(args.iteration) || args.iteration < 1) { process.stderr.write('--iteration must be a positive integer\\n'); return 2; }\n178: \n179:   const result = verify(args.loopType, args.artifactDir, args.iteration);\n180:   if (args.json) {\n181:     process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(result)}\\n`);\n182:   } else if (result.ok) {\n183:     process.stdout.write(`OK ${result.detail}\\n`);\n184:   } else {\n185:     process.stderr.write(`${result.reason} ${result.detail}\\n`);\n186:   }\n187:   return result.ok ? 0 : 1;\n188: }\n189: \n190: if (require.main === module) {\n191:   process.exit(main());\n192: }\n193: \n194: module.exports = { verify, checkRouteProof, findIterationNarrative, readJsonlRecords, pad3, REASONS, LEAF_BY_LOOP, STATE_LOG_BY_LOOP };\n\n(End of file - total 194 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"#!/usr/bin/env node\n'use strict';\n\n// After-dispatch leaf-reliability check for the deep-loop iteration loop.\n//\n// A dispatched leaf owes THREE artifacts per iteration: the narrative markdown\n// (iterations/iteration-NNN.md), an appended canonical state-log record, and a\n// per-iteration delta file. The state-log record must also carry route-proof\n// fields proving the leaf ran as itself (mode, target_agent, agent_definition_loaded,\n// resolved_route). A model-driven loop is trusted to self-check today, which lets a\n// silently-incomplete leaf advance the loop. This makes the check mechanical: exit\n// non-zero with a single machine reason so the workflow can re-dispatch the same\n// iteration once before recording an error and continuing.\n\nconst fs = require('node:fs');\nconst path = require('node:path');\n\nconst LEAF_BY_LOOP = {\n  review: 'deep-review',\n  research: 'deep-research',","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/verify-iteration.cjs","text":"#!/usr/bin/env node\n'use strict';\n\n// After-dispatch leaf-reliability check for the deep-loop iteration loop.\n//\n// A dispatched leaf owes THREE artifacts per iteration: the narrative markdown\n// (iterations/iteration-NNN.md), an appended canonical state-log record, and a\n// per-iteration delta file. The state-log record must also carry route-proof\n// fields proving the leaf ran as itself (mode, target_agent, agent_definition_loaded,\n// resolved_route). A model-driven loop is trusted to self-check today, which lets a\n// silently-incomplete leaf advance the loop. This makes the check mechanical: exit\n// non-zero with a single machine reason so the workflow can re-dispatch the same\n// iteration once before recording an error and continuing.\n\nconst fs = require('node:fs');\nconst path = require('node:path');\n\nconst LEAF_BY_LOOP = {\n  review: 'deep-review',\n  research: 'deep-research',\n};\n\nconst STATE_LOG_BY_LOOP = {\n  review: 'deep-review-state.jsonl',\n  research: 'deep-research-state.jsonl',\n};\n\nconst REASONS = {\n  ITERATION_FILE_MISSING: 'iteration_file_missing',\n  ITERATION_VERDICT_MISSING: 'iteration_verdict_missing',\n  STATE_RECORD_MISSING: 'state_record_missing',\n  ROUTE_PROOF_MISSING: 'route_proof_missing',\n  ROUTE_PROOF_MISMATCH: 'route_proof_mismatch',\n  DELTA_FILE_MISSING: 'delta_file_missing',\n};\n\nfunction pad3(n) {\n  return String(n).padStart(3, '0');\n}\n\nfunction parseArgs(argv) {\n  const out = { json: false };\n  for (let i = 0; i < argv.length; i += 1) {\n    const a = argv[i];\n    if (a === '--loop-type') { out.loopType = argv[i + 1]; i += 1; }\n    else if (a === '--artifact-dir') { out.artifactDir = argv[i + 1]; i += 1; }\n    else if (a === '--iteration') { out.iteration = parseInt(argv[i + 1], 10); i += 1; }\n    else if (a === '--json') { out.json = true; }\n    else if (a === '--help' || a === '-h') { out.help = true; }\n    else { out.error = `unknown flag: ${a}`; }\n  }\n  return out;\n}\n\n// Read a JSONL file and return parsed objects, skipping blank/malformed lines so a\n// single corrupt append never crashes the gate.\nfunction readJsonlRecords(filePath) {\n  let raw;\n  try {\n    raw = fs.readFileSync(filePath, 'utf8');\n  } catch (_) {\n    return null; // file absent/unreadable\n  }\n  const records = [];\n  for (const line of raw.split('\\n')) {\n    const trimmed = line.trim();\n    if (!trimmed) continue;\n    try {\n      records.push(JSON.parse(trimmed));\n    } catch (_) {\n      // skip malformed line\n    }\n  }\n  return records;\n}\n\n// The narrative file is written as iteration-NNN.md but the leaf may append a\n// descriptive suffix (iteration-NNN-some-focus.md), so match the padded number as a\n// prefix bounded by \".\" or \"-\" to avoid confusing 002 with 020.\nfunction findIterationNarrative(iterationsDir, iteration) {\n  const nnn = pad3(iteration);\n  let entries;\n  try {\n    entries = fs.readdirSync(iterationsDir);\n  } catch (_) {\n    return null;\n  }\n  const re = new RegExp(`^iteration-${nnn}(?:\\\\.md$|-.*\\\\.md$)`);\n  for (const name of entries) {\n    if (re.test(name)) return path.join(iterationsDir, name);\n  }\n  return null;\n}\n\nfunction isNonEmptyString(value) {\n  return typeof value === 'string' && value.trim().length > 0;\n}\n\n// Route-proof lives on the canonical iteration record. Absent fields => the leaf did\n// not emit route-proof at all; present-but-wrong => it ran as something other than\n// its own leaf identity or in the wrong mode.\nfunction checkRouteProof(record, loopType, leaf) {\n  const hasMode = 'mode' in record;\n  const hasTarget = 'target_agent' in record;\n  const hasLoaded = 'agent_definition_loaded' in record;\n  const hasRoute = 'resolved_route' in record;\n  if (!hasMode || !hasTarget || !hasLoaded || !hasRoute) {\n    return REASONS.ROUTE_PROOF_MISSING;\n  }\n  if (\n    record.mode !== loopType ||\n    record.target_agent !== leaf ||\n    record.agent_definition_loaded !== true ||\n    !isNonEmptyString(record.resolved_route)\n  ) {\n    return REASONS.ROUTE_PROOF_MISMATCH;\n  }\n  return null;\n}\n\nfunction verify(loopType, artifactDir, iteration) {\n  const leaf = LEAF_BY_LOOP[loopType];\n  const stateLogName = STATE_LOG_BY_LOOP[loopType];\n\n  // 1. Iteration narrative markdown.\n  const narrativePath = findIterationNarrative(path.join(artifactDir, 'iterations'), iteration);\n  if (!narrativePath) {\n    return { ok: false, reason: REASONS.ITERATION_FILE_MISSING, detail: `no iterations/iteration-${pad3(iteration)}*.md under ${artifactDir}` };\n  }\n  const narrative = fs.readFileSync(narrativePath, 'utf8');\n  if (!narrative.trim()) {\n    return { ok: false, reason: REASONS.ITERATION_FILE_MISSING, detail: `${narrativePath} is empty` };\n  }\n  // Review narratives must end on a machine-readable verdict; research/context use a\n  // different closing shape, so only review enforces the verdict line here.\n  if (loopType === 'review' && !/Review verdict:\\s*(PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL)/i.test(narrative)) {\n    return { ok: false, reason: REASONS.ITERATION_VERDICT_MISSING, detail: `${narrativePath} lacks a \"Review verdict: PASS|CONDITIONAL|FAIL\" line` };\n  }\n\n  // 2. Canonical state-log record for this iteration + route-proof.\n  const stateRecords = readJsonlRecords(path.join(artifactDir, stateLogName));\n  // Review/research key the iteration number as `iteration`; context keys it as `run`.\n  // Match either so one shim covers all three modes (a non-numeric run-id yields NaN\n  // and never false-matches). Take the LAST matching record, not the first: the state\n  // log is append-only, so a re-dispatched iteration appends a corrected record after\n  // the bad one -- matching the first would keep reporting the stale failure and defeat\n  // the bounded retry. The state reducer applies the same latest-record-wins rule.\n  const iterationRecord = (stateRecords || []).findLast(\n    (r) => r && r.type === 'iteration' && (Number(r.iteration) === iteration || Number(r.run) === iteration),\n  );\n  if (!iterationRecord) {\n    return { ok: false, reason: REASONS.STATE_RECORD_MISSING, detail: `no type=iteration record with iteration=${iteration} in ${stateLogName}` };\n  }\n  const routeReason = checkRouteProof(iterationRecord, loopType, leaf);\n  if (routeReason) {\n    return { ok: false, reason: routeReason, detail: `iteration ${iteration} state record failed route-proof (expected mode=${loopType} target_agent=${leaf})` };\n  }\n\n  // 3. Per-iteration delta file with at least one iteration record.\n  const deltaRecords = readJsonlRecords(path.join(artifactDir, 'deltas', `iter-${pad3(iteration)}.jsonl`));\n  if (!deltaRecords || !deltaRecords.some((r) => r && r.type === 'iteration')) {\n    return { ok: false, reason: REASONS.DELTA_FILE_MISSING, detail: `deltas/iter-${pad3(iteration)}.jsonl missing or has no type=iteration record` };\n  }\n\n  return { ok: true, reason: null, detail: `iteration ${iteration} complete: narrative + route-proof + delta` };\n}\n\nfunction main(argv = process.argv.slice(2)) {\n  const args = parseArgs(argv);\n  if (args.help) {\n    process.stdout.write('Usage: verify-iteration.cjs --loop-type review|research|context --artifact-dir <dir> --iteration <N> [--json]\\n');\n    return 0;\n  }\n  if (args.error) { process.stderr.write(`${args.error}\\n`); return 2; }\n  if (!args.loopType || !LEAF_BY_LOOP[args.loopType]) { process.stderr.write('--loop-type must be one of review|research\\n'); return 2; }\n  if (!args.artifactDir) { process.stderr.write('--artifact-dir is required\\n'); return 2; }\n  if (!Number.isInteger(args.iteration) || args.iteration < 1) { process.stderr.write('--iteration must be a positive integer\\n'); return 2; }\n\n  const result = verify(args.loopType, args.artifactDir, args.iteration);\n  if (args.json) {\n    process.stdout.write(`${JSON.stringify(result)}\\n`);\n  } else if (result.ok) {\n    process.stdout.write(`OK ${result.detail}\\n`);\n  } else {\n    process.stderr.write(`${result.reason} ${result.detail}\\n`);\n  }\n  return result.ok ? 0 : 1;\n}\n\nif (require.main === module) {\n  process.exit(main());\n}\n\nmodule.exports = { verify, checkRouteProof, findIterationNarrative, readJsonlRecords, pad3, REASONS, LEAF_BY_LOOP, STATE_LOG_BY_LOOP };","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":194,"totalLines":194,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/verify-iteration.cjs","time":{"start":1783489694617,"end":1783489694623}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0d603b1683f4755e016a4de49e764881919c186ad2d3e2857c"}},"id":"prt_f40450b90001WBctEFsHpEhHhQ","sessionID":"ses_0bfc4afb7ffeA8X2g5OnaG20YL","messageID":"msg_f4044d0c5001HtMB4qPNkZw60i"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783489694643,"sessionID":"ses_0bfc4afb7ffeA8X2g5OnaG20YL","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_EDOVFwRqMCQdJMvZbxA2cERD","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-10/deep-research-state.jsonl","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-10/deep-research-state.jsonl</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"Validate and stress-test the merge design for folding deep-loop-runtime into deep-loop-workflows as system-deep-loop: structural layout, bidirectional path-coupling repair, the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow, reference migration across commands/agents/READMEs/advisor-corpus, and whether fallback-router.ts should be wired for real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback.\",\"maxIterations\":10,\"minIterations\":3,\"convergenceThreshold\":0.05,\"convergenceMode\":\"default\",\"stopPolicy\":\"convergence\",\"minIdeaObservations\":2,\"resource_map_present\":false,\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":true},\"createdAt\":\"2026-07-08T05:41:43Z\",\"specFolder\":\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-10-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n2: {\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"artifact_boundary_notice\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":0,\"detail\":\"Bound artifact_dir directly to config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir; skipped resolveArtifactRoot and all writes outside the lineage directory.\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:41:43Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-10-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n3: {\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"spec_check_result\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"normalized_topic\":\"validate and stress-test the merge design for folding deep-loop-runtime into deep-loop-workflows as system-deep-loop structural layout bidirectional path-coupling repair the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow reference migration across commands agents readmes advisor-corpus and whether fallback-router ts should be wired for real glm-5 2 to mimo-v2 5-pro fallback\",\"specPath\":\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/spec.md\",\"writeback\":\"deferred_lineage_boundary\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:41:43Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-10-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n4: {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":1,\"iteration\":1,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Establish charter, scope, and phase decomposition\",\"findingsCount\":4,\"newInfoRatio\":1.0,\"noveltyJustification\":\"First pass established the packet scope, the read-only constraint, and the five stress-test axes.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Is the structural layout sound?\",\"Are bidirectional path-coupling rules correct?\",\"Is the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow accounted for?\",\"Are all external references and advisor surfaces covered?\",\"Should fallback-router.ts be wired for GLM-5.2 to MiMo fallback?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Research charter and scope confirmed from the packet.\"],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"finding-charter-readonly\",\"title\":\"Reference research is explicitly read-only and must feed 002/003 rather than mutate the merge itself\",\"summary\":\"The packet says the research fanout validates the merge design and explicitly excludes executing the merge or modifying deep-loop-workflows/deep-loop-runtime.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/spec.md:57\",\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/spec.md:69\",\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/spec.md:73\"]}],\"durationMs\":120000,\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:41:43Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-10-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n5: {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":2,\"iteration\":2,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Validate structural layout and runtime nesting\",\"findingsCount\":4,\"newInfoRatio\":0.82,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Confirmed the proposed topology and found one category-error guard worth preserving in implementation.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Is the structural layout sound?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Structural layout is sound if runtime remains infrastructure, not a workflowMode.\"],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"finding-runtime-not-mode\",\"title\":\"runtime/ must be infrastructure, not an eighth mode\",\"summary\":\"The proposed tree nests the former runtime under system-deep-loop/runtime and explicitly says adding runtime as a mode-registry entry would be a category error.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:157\",\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:163\",\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:169\"]}],\"durationMs\":115000,\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:41:43Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-10-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n6: {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":3,\"iteration\":3,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Stress-test bidirectional path-coupling repair\",\"findingsCount\":5,\"newInfoRatio\":0.76,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Confirmed the asymmetric path rule and elevated it as the central execution invariant.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Are bidirectional path-coupling rules correct?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"The forward and reverse directions require different repairs, not one global substitution.\"],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"finding-asymmetric-coupling\",\"title\":\"Path repair is intentionally asymmetric\",\"summary\":\"Forward runtime-to-workflow references keep hop count and delete the old workflow segment; reverse workflow-to-runtime references move one hop nearer and rename the segment.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:58\",\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:72\",\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:173\",\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:174\"]}],\"durationMs\":118000,\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:41:43Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-10-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n7: {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":4,\"iteration\":4,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Verify the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow is load-bearing\",\"findingsCount\":5,\"newInfoRatio\":0.7,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Connected the phase plan to the live package and vitest config paths that will break after nesting if not repaired.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Is the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow accounted for?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"The tooling-borrow is correctly scoped into 002 and includes both runtime and system-spec-kit sides.\"],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"finding-tooling-borrow-load-bearing\",\"title\":\"The tooling-borrow is not documentation; it gates runtime typecheck and council tests\",\"summary\":\"Runtime package scripts borrow tsc from system-spec-kit, tsconfig borrows @types from system-spec-kit, and system-spec-kit vitest includes deep-loop-runtime tests by relative path.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:73\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/package.json:11\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tsconfig.json:12\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts:18\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts:20\"]}],\"durationMs\":121000,\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:41:43Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-10-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n8: {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":5,\"iteration\":5,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Inventory executable command and agent reference migration surfaces\",\"findingsCount\":5,\"newInfoRatio\":0.66,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Expanded external migration beyond docs into command assets, doctor routes, and mirrored agents.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Are all external references covered?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Commands, doctor routes, and both agent trees are explicit migration surfaces.\"],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"finding-command-agent-surfaces\",\"title\":\"External migration is executable, not just prose\",\"summary\":\"Doctor deep-loop route invokes runtime scripts directly, deep command YAMLs cite both workflow and runtime paths, and OpenCode/Claude agent mirrors carry registry and script references.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/commands/doctor/_routes.yaml:108\",\".opencode/commands/doctor/_routes.yaml:110\",\".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_ai-council_confirm.yaml:40\",\".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_ai-council_confirm.yaml:47\",\".opencode/agents/orchestrate.md:185\",\".claude/agents/orchestrate.md:174\"]}],\"durationMs\":117000,\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:41:43Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-10-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n9: {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":6,\"iteration\":6,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Stress-test advisor projection, corpus, and graph migration\",\"findingsCount\":6,\"newInfoRatio\":0.62,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Found the highest-risk migration bundle: generated projection hash, hand constants, lexical boosts, graph edges, and divergence fixtures.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Are advisor surfaces covered?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Advisor migration must be staged with baseline, codegen, drift guard, corpus, and divergence ratchet.\"],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"finding-advisor-high-risk\",\"title\":\"Advisor migration is the highest-risk reference area\",\"summary\":\"The advisor hardcodes the deep-loop mode registry path, carries generated alias projection and hash, defines MERGED_DEEP_SKILL_ID, and has separate explicit scoring literals that still target deep-loop-workflows.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py:83\",\".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/aliases.ts:21\",\".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/aliases.ts:23\",\".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/aliases.ts:109\",\".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/lanes/explicit.ts:28\",\".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/lanes/explicit.ts:31\"]}],\"durationMs\":123000,\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:41:43Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-10-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n10: {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":7,\"iteration\":7,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Evaluate fallback-router wiring for GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro\",\"findingsCount\":5,\"newInfoRatio\":0.52,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Confirmed the router can enforce approved cross-pool fallback, but the fanout pool currently only retries same lineage attempts.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Should fallback-router.ts be wired for GLM-5.2 to MiMo fallback?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Fallback wiring is valuable but should remain optional unless the operator accepts feature scope.\"],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"finding-fallback-optional-real-caller\",\"title\":\"fallback-router.ts is ready for a real caller but fanout-pool does not call it today\",\"summary\":\"fallback-router resolves approved cross-pool fallbacks, while fanout-pool only schedules retries and marks retry_exhausted after maxRetries. The optional phase's success criterion is simply making fallback-router.ts have a non-test caller.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:357\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:376\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:400\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:628\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:650\",\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md:104\"]}],\"durationMs\":116000,\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:41:43Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-10-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n11: {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":8,\"iteration\":8,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Check GLM and MiMo model registry facts against the fallback question\",\"findingsCount\":4,\"newInfoRatio\":0.35,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Mostly confirmed known fallback constraints with model-profile evidence and clarified the approved-target requirement.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Can GLM-5.2 safely fall back to MiMo-v2.5-Pro?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"A GLM-to-MiMo route is technically possible only after explicit registry/config approval and smoke-tested provider availability.\"],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"finding-glm-mimo-fallback-needs-approval\",\"title\":\"GLM and MiMo are separate active pools, but neither profile declares fallback_target today\",\"summary\":\"MiMo uses xiaomi-token-plan, GLM uses zai-coding-plan, and both have fallback_target null; automatic GLM-to-MiMo would be new policy, not a latent default.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:190\",\".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:203\",\".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:204\",\".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:255\",\".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:268\",\".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/assets/model_profiles.json:269\"]}],\"durationMs\":109000,\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:41:43Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-10-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n12: {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":9,\"iteration\":9,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Validate 003 staging and residual-reference exit gates\",\"findingsCount\":4,\"newInfoRatio\":0.18,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Low novelty; the external migration plan already contains the right staging and exit gates, but they are mandatory risk controls.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Are external reference migration gates sufficient?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"003's staged plan is sufficient if baseline and post-change accuracy gates are treated as blockers.\"],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"finding-003-gates-sufficient\",\"title\":\"003 has the right dependency ordering and exit gates\",\"summary\":\"The external migration plan requires grep-before/after bracketing, hardcoded constants before generated fields, command-contract regeneration, agent mirror sync, graph edge collapse, advisor corpus re-baseline, and an 11-step exit gate.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/plan.md:67\",\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/plan.md:75\",\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/plan.md:84\",\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/plan.md:95\",\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/plan.md:101\",\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/plan.md:106\"]}],\"convergenceSignals\":{\"rollingAvg\":0.35,\"madScore\":0.385,\"entropyCoverage\":0.8,\"compositeStop\":0.35},\"durationMs\":103000,\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:41:43Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-10-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n13: {\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":10,\"iteration\":10,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Final convergence check and ranked recommendation\",\"findingsCount\":4,\"newInfoRatio\":0.06,\"noveltyJustification\":\"Only marginal new information remained; this iteration confirmed recommendations and recorded negative knowledge.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Is the merge design ready to proceed?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Proceed with 002 and 003 as designed; keep 004 optional unless the operator explicitly wants automatic fallback feature work bundled.\"],\"keyFindings\":[{\"id\":\"finding-proceed-with-guardrails\",\"title\":\"Proceed with 002 and 003, do not silently fold optional fallback into the merge\",\"summary\":\"The core move/reference-migration plan is sound. fallback-router wiring is real but optional feature scope, with its own success criteria and open operator question.\",\"sources\":[\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:77\",\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:78\",\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md:115\",\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md:123\"]}],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Naive global string replacement\",\"reason\":\"Forward and reverse coupling require different relative-depth repairs.\",\"evidence\":\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:173\"},{\"approach\":\"Make runtime an eighth workflowMode\",\"reason\":\"The target spec says runtime is infrastructure, not a workflowMode.\",\"evidence\":\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/002-hub-rename-and-runtime-nesting/spec.md:169\"},{\"approach\":\"Silently auto-wire GLM to MiMo fallback during 002/003\"... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n14: {\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_synthesis_deferred\",\"reason\":\"Detached lineage boundary forbids writes outside artifact_dir; research.md is canonical for this lineage.\",\"generatedFence\":\"deep-research/spec-findings\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-07-08T05:41:43Z\",\"sessionId\":\"fanout-gpt55-fast-10-1783486518892-2qss01\",\"generation\":1}\n15: {\"ty