-|----------|--------------------|\n37: | **[P0]** | HARD BLOCKER | Cannot claim done until complete |\n38: | **[P1]** | Required | Must complete OR get user approval |\n39: | **[P2]** | Optional | Can defer with documented reason |\n40: <!-- /ANCHOR:protocol -->\n41: \n42: ---\n43: \n44: <!-- ANCHOR:pre-impl -->\n45: ## Pre-Implementation\n46: \n47: - [ ] CHK-001 [P0] `sonnet5` lineage smoke-tested at `count: 1` before committing all 5 replicas\n48: - [ ] CHK-002 [P1] No stale writer-lock files under `deep-loop-runtime/database/` before dispatch\n49: <!-- /ANCHOR:pre-impl -->\n50: \n51: ---\n52: \n53: <!-- ANCHOR:code-quality -->\n54: ## Code Quality\n55: \n56: - [ ] CHK-010 [P1] The `--executors` JSON payload uses the correct field names (`iterations` not `iters`) and kinds (`cli-claude-code` for Sonnet-5, never `native`)\n57: <!-- /ANCHOR:code-quality -->\n58: \n59: ---\n60: \n61: <!-- ANCHOR:testing -->\n62: ## Testing\n63: \n64: - [ ] CHK-020 [P0] All 20 replicas dispatched exactly as specified (10 gpt55-fast, 5 glm52, 5 sonnet5)\n65: - [ ] CHK-021 [P0] Every completed replica reached `minIterations: 3`\n66: - [ ] CHK-022 [P1] All 3 lineages produced at least one completed replica\n67: <!-- /ANCHOR:testing -->\n68: \n69: ---\n70: \n71: <!-- ANCHOR:fix-completeness -->\n72: ## Fix Completeness\n73: \n74: - [ ] CHK-P0-001 [P0] Every finding in `research/research.md` cites which lineage/replica surfaced it and a concrete file:line or artifact reference\n75: - [ ] CHK-P1-002 [P1] GLM-5.2 failures handled gracefully (salvage or manual re-dispatch), not silently dropped\n76: <!-- /ANCHOR:fix-completeness -->\n77: \n78: ---\n79: \n80: <!-- ANCHOR:security -->\n81: ## Security\n82: \n83: - [ ] CHK-030 [P2] No file modification outside `research/` — this phase is strictly read-only investigation\n84: <!-- /ANCHOR:security -->\n85: \n86: ---\n87: \n88: <!-- ANCHOR:docs -->\n89: ## Documentation\n90: \n91: - [ ] CHK-040 [P0] `research/research.md` synthesized with ranked,